Я умею работать в любых условиях)
Самое главное-результат. 
Мы собираем торты и в шикарных ресторанах на оборудованных кухнях и на улице и даже в багажнике автомобиля. Нас не пугает двадцатиградусный холод и тридцатиградусная жара. 

Эта свадьба проходила в самом центре города с шикарным видом , но из-за сложности выноса  собирала прям на месте  выездной церемонии .  В тот день был сумасшедший ветер. Декор улетал с торта и даже стол катился  по подиуму ( если посмотрите фото в конце, там жених придерживает) . Но мы справились.

Cake Design No. 2 “Nazrahna”

When I started making cakes my dad would buy me anything to do with baking, and he still does. Some cake tools I’d never seen before and had no idea of its use. 

One time Nazrahna was at mine and she saw a cake tool in my house. When we went cake shopping she saw that tool at the shop and she said “Hallu, this tool what your dads brought for you is expensive, look after it and figure out how to use it” and now atleast 10 years later I’ve used it so much. 
And she doesn’t remember what she said but because she reminded me I’ve learnt its use and used it soo much and thought of her everytime I used it!  

So hears Nazrahna  isn’t she gorgeous? Just like my friend Najju 

Ill pop a picture of the tool on my story soon if you haven’t got, its an excellent buy, you’ll always have uniform ropes etc and can thank me later x

Llevo una buena semana hablando de libros con mi madre. 

Nos intercambiamos y regalamos con premura, como si en ellos estuviera “eso” que nos falta. 

Ella está ahora viajando a Japón gracias a “Soy un gato” y “El crisantelmo y la espada” y yo acabo de reponorme del “Reencuentro” de Fred Uhlman y he vuelto a La Comarca con Bilbo Bolsón, que siempre me ha hecho feliz. 

Y hoy, Juan José Millás en su columna de @el_pais habla sobre los lugares a los que llegamos dentro de un libro. 

Habla de una chica anónima con la que compartía vagón de Metro. 

“Todos íbamos dentro de un vehículo menos ella, que iba dentro de un libro.”

Elena, la protagonista de las fotos y ese vestido hipnótico, llevó sus alianzas en un libro de Harry Potter. 

“Yo he llegado a todas partes dentro de un libro, pero a veces lo olvido y me empeño en llegar de otros modos” concluye Millás.

 کیک عروسی همیشه سفیدِ سفید نیست! 

کیک‌های عروسی می‌توانند ترکیبی از رنگ‌های 
سفید و طلایی یا حتی رنگ‌های متنوع دیگری باشند! 
در این آلبوم، مجموعه‌ای از کیک‌های عروسی کوچک و بزرگ 
را می‌بینید که با رنگ طلایی جذاب‌تر شده‌اند. 
برخی با ترکیب سفید و طلایی طراحی شده‌اند و 
برخی دیگر با رنگ‌های ملایم مثل صورتی، آبی، 
سبز و... که جلوه‌ای خاص خودشون رو دارند .

اما چیزی که این کیک‌ها را خاص می‌کند، 
سلیقه‌ی شخصی عروس و داماد و داستانی است 
که برای طراحی مراسمشان انتخاب کرده‌اند. 
هر کیک یک روایت دارد؛ 
روایتی از عشق، سلیقه و لحظه‌های ناب زندگی شما!

What's the number one thing you look for when you're searching for the perfect photographer/videographer? Is it price, style, location, personality, etc? If you've been looking for a photographer/videographer you've probably realized that it can be a little overwhelming at times and I'm here to help you in your search with my 5 best tips on finding the perfect duo! 

If you're a photographer you might mention that they should view their portfolio to see if they have the right style, or that cheaper prices can sometimes be a red flag]

1. View an entire wedding gallery/video done by them 
2. Don’t ever book a photographer/videographer without FaceTiming them first
3. Pay attention to their style and make sure they are exactly what you’re wanting
4. Sticking to your budget is important, but just remember you get what you pay for 
5. Ask them about their experience and what value they bring to the table 

I hope these little tips help you with your search. If you'd love to talk more about hiring us as your photo/video duo then fill out our inquiry page in our bio! مگنوس کارلسن، شطرنج باز شماره‌ی یک جهان که عنوان استاد شطرنج ( Chess Grandmaster) را داراست در یک مراسم خصوصی در اسلو با الا ویکتوریا عروسی کرد✨️

مگنوس کارلسن ۳۴ ساله و اهل نروژ است که پنج بار قهرمان جهان شده و رکورد‌های جهانی زیادی هم داره، او مدتی بود که با اِلا رابطه‌ی دوستی داشته و در عروسیشان علاوه بر مهمانان گروهی از فیلمبرداران نت‌فیلیکس هم برای مستندسازی حضور داشتند.

این دو که در کلیسا عروسی کردند، بعد از مراسم در هتل پنج ستاره نمادین اسلو به پذیرایی و جشن پرداختند که در بین مهمانان شطرنج‌بازان معروف جهان مثل جان لودویگ همر و ... در مراسم حضور داشتند.

لباس عروس اِلا ترکیبی از پارچه‌ی دانتل و ساتن بود که دامن حجیمی داشت و یقه‌ی آن بسته بود، برای این مدل یقه معمولا جواهراتی در قسمت گردن استفاده نمی‌شه که عروس هم از این قاعده پیروی کرده بود.

میکاپ و مدل موی عروس هم خیلی ساده انتخاب شده بود و تناژ رنگی میکاپ عروس صورتی/هلویی بود که جزو میکاپ‌های ترند عروس هستش

عروسی این دو، دقیقا چند روز بعد از اخراج مگنوس از مسابقات جهانی قهرمانی بلیتز بود که از هفته‌های پیش اعلام کرده بود در این تورنمنت جهانی حضور خواهد داشت.

زمانی که او برای این مسابقه با شلوار جین حضور پیدا کرد (۲۷ دسامبر)، هیئت حاکمه به او گفته بود که نمیتونه با شلوار جین مسابقه بده❗️

بعد از واکنش‌های شدید، مسابقه اعلام کرده بود که قوانینش برای پوشش را تغییر میده و شلوار جین را مجاز می‌کنه، مگنوس هم که در روزهای آینده به مسابقه بازخواهد گشت، اعلام کرده که شلوار جین قراره بپوشه

I wanted to spend my special day with my family, siblings, friends and the love of my life with dancing, laughing, singing and thats exactly how it went. What's the number one thing you look for when you're searching for the perfect photographer/videographer? Is it price, style, location, personality, etc? If you've been looking for a photographer/videographer you've probably realized that it can be a little overwhelming at times and I'm here to help you in your search with my 5 best tips on finding the perfect duo! 

If you're a photographer you might mention that they should view their portfolio to see if they have the right style, or that cheaper prices can sometimes be a red flag]

1. View an entire wedding gallery/video done by them 
2. Don’t ever book a photographer/videographer without FaceTiming them first
3. Pay attention to their style and make sure they are exactly what you’re wanting
4. Sticking to your budget is important, but just remember you get what you pay for 
5. Ask them about their experience and what value they bring to the table 

I hope these little tips help you with your search. If you'd love to talk more about hiring us as your photo/video duo then fill out our inquiry page in our bio! We have a few available spots to FaceTime within the next week or two! We would love to send you some more information to see if we'd be a great fit!

Brooke + Jake by Georgia Munns - Our ideal date night could be anything from a trendy restaurant to riding our bikes barefoot to the local surfy. We both come from the restaurant industry—Jake is the chef, and I am the front-of-house. The four settings we reset before every wedding day

The first step is to reset our White balance to 5200

Next we sync all our camera clocks, so images appear in perfect chronological order.

Resetting the file count keeps all our images in order by file name and is an extra check at the end of the night. We know we’ve loaded 100% of the images, by checking the total image count and the file name of the last image taken

Finally, a quick check that we are recording to multiple cards and playing back to the SD. Since we load from our SDs we want to ensure any ratings made in-camera transfer to the catalog

A quick tip, never forget a step, by configuring your camera’s custom menu to display all the settings you use to reset your camera.

That was episode 140 - We’re Jeff and Cat and if you liked this style of learning, give us a follow and we’ll see you on the next one.

If you're a photographer you might mention that they should view their portfolio to see if they have the right style, or that cheaper prices can sometimes be a red flag]

1. View an entire wedding gallery/video done by them 
2. Don’t ever book a photographer/videographer without FaceTiming them first
3. Pay attention to their style and make sure they are exactly what you’re wanting
4. Sticking to your budget is important, but just remember you get what you pay for 
5. Ask them about their experience and what value they bring to the table

Planning your wedding? Let us create your happily-ever-after on any budget! 

Day 1: Arrival & Celebration  Welcome to Foreverland!
 12:00 PM - Arrival & Check-In: Guests are greeted with personalized welcome kits at a boutique heritage resort. Think vibrant mehendi cones, a little luxury, and a whole lot of love!

4:00 PM - Mehendi & High Tea: A boho-themed setup with marigold decor, fairy lights, and cozy seating. Add live folk music and a chai-tapas station for a delightful vibe.

7:00 PM - Sangeet Night: The big fat Bollywood dance-off! A stunning stage, LED screens, and a rocking DJ set the tone. Dinner: A mix of Indian, Italian, and Asian cuisines to please every palate.

Day 2: The Big Day  Say “I Do” with Glam!

8:00 AM - Haldi Ceremony: Poolside fun with turmeric, flower showers, and traditional music. Serve refreshing mocktails and fresh fruits.

11:00 AM - Brunch: A chic brunch with live stations for dosas, waffles, and artisanal coffees. Perfect for Instagram moments!

5:00 PM - Wedding Ceremony: A sunset mandap adorned with pastel florals overlooking the lake. The baraat enters with a twist—a vintage car followed by dhol and nagadas!

8:00 PM - Reception: A starry night with a mix of elegance and fun. Twinkling fairy lights, a live band, and a delicious multi-cuisine dinner with a grand dessert bar.

10:00 PM - Afterparty: Close the night with a rooftop afterparty—cocktails, a DJ, and dancing under the stars!
 All of this in just ₹30 Lakhs! Swipe to discover how we make dream weddings come true.

I feel like this is one of the most requested half a hairstyles whether you are a bride or a bridesmaid in here is how simple it is to do. Just please remember just because the styling steps are simple that does not mean you can skip the prep. The prep is where the style comes together. Make sure you are starting with a smooth, clean canvas and take your time with the curls. If you find that your curls are immediately falling out as you’re styling I always suggest to go to a smaller size barrel.

Meet Deji Rachel, a talented makeup artist who has spent nearly a decade serving over 400 brides and countless clients worldwide. From her humble beginnings with a few makeup brushes to becoming a judge at The National Wedding Awards and working with industry giants like Chanel 4, Deji’s journey is nothing short of inspiring.

Her story is one of faith, family, passion, and purpose. With a heart for people and a commitment to excellence, she believes that success isn’t just about skills—it’s about character and integrity. Deji’s artistry goes beyond makeup; it’s about making brides feel confident, radiant, and celebrated on their special day.

I love, love, love me a beautiful, fall wedding. I can’t get enough of how fall foliage transforms floral designs with both color and movement. Oftentimes, we’re out in the woods trying to find that perfect pairing of fall foliage for our fall wedding couples, where the leaves are not only  the perfect shades of fall but also haven’t lost all their leaves entirely and are willing to hold on to them for just a little longer. Albert Cames may have said it best when he said “Autumn is a second spring when every leaf is a flower.”

Could this be the prettiest marquee florals you’ve ever seen? Yes, I would agree it probably is…

..

An absolute highlight of last season was to work on this private marquee wedding near Englefield Estate with a stellar team of vendors. @katrinaotterwed planned and styled the event so beautifully as always. We dreamt up a blush pink colour palette that wasn’t overly sweet and had a modern look, whilst still feeling very naturalistic and garden inspired. Emphasis on bespoke and original design as well as the pursuit of new ideas is integral to my work and I was delighted that Kat wanted to push the florals out of the comfort zone. The sweet meadows that adorned the tables were full to the brim with British grown garden roses and all  the bouncy cosmos was especially grown for us by one of our local growers. The marquee was filled with an incredible scent of roses, jasmine and sweet peas. My heart will be forever full of love for these tables and I am incredibly grateful that we could be part of this family celebration and team of suppliers.

A beautiful white dahlia as snow is coming to North Carolina.  This first-year dahlia seedling did not bloom until the beginning of October.  The bloom size was around 5 inches across.  The seed parent is one of my dahlias from seed.  I hope the tubers store well over the winter as I would like to pay more attention to this seedling this year.  It had a great petal count with the petals flowing back to the stem.  Our temperatures have been below average this winter so the snow is going to stick when it arrives this afternoon.  We may have three inches or more of snow.  Stay warm & safe.  The snow will be pretty; however, I just keep planning for spring!  #lovegrowingflowers #flowersforacoldday #readyforspring #firstyeardahliaseedling #whitedahlia #dahliasaremyfavorite

Llevo una buena semana hablando de libros con mi madre. 

Nos intercambiamos y regalamos con premura, como si en ellos estuviera “eso” que nos falta. 

Ella está ahora viajando a Japón gracias a “Soy un gato” y “El crisantelmo y la espada” y yo acabo de reponorme del “Reencuentro” de Fred Uhlman y he vuelto a La Comarca con Bilbo Bolsón, que siempre me ha hecho feliz. 

Y hoy, Juan José Millás en su columna de @el_pais habla sobre los lugares a los que llegamos dentro de un libro. 

Habla de una chica anónima con la que compartía vagón de Metro. 

“Todos íbamos dentro de un vehículo menos ella, que iba dentro de un libro.”

Elena, la protagonista de las fotos y ese vestido hipnótico, llevó sus alianzas en un libro de Harry Potter. 

“Yo he llegado a todas partes dentro de un libro, pero a veces lo olvido y me empeño en llegar de otros modos” concluye Millás.

For those that are married, what is your biggest regret from your wedding? Something you wished you did/had or maybe you wished you didn’t do? It’s hard when you’re deep in planning, you think everything is so important but I feel like after the fact there’s so much you didn’t need or didn’t notice?

It’s seeming like it’s very easy to get out of control and I only plan on getting married once ;) so I want to nail it with no regrets.

Today is WEDDING WEDNESDAY.  The tradition of a white (shades of ivory, cream and ecru also) wedding dress in Victorian times is commonly credited to Queen Victoria’s choice to wear a white (an ivory) wedding dress at her wedding to Prince Albert in 1840
.
Edwardian wedding dresses were often  characterized by lots of lace,a blouson bodice and A line skirts. 
.
English Wedding dress with a cream silk bodice and skirt,1902
.
Houghton & Dalton (designer and maker)
.
Made from cream Silk and Lace
.
Worn by Edith Constance Jardine Hope-Murray on the occasion of her marriage to Mr. T.H. Senior, 18 June 1902.
.
Shown with veil
.
That bodice is simply gorgeous!!!

Tomi and Derin (who first met at a mutual friend’s book club on Emergent Strategy by Adrienne Maree Brown), celebrated their love in an amazing two-day destination wedding hosted at The Rich Hippies House in West Palm Beach.⁠
⁠
On Friday evening, the couple hosted an intimate traditional Yoruba engagement ceremony paying tribute to their shared Nigerian roots. "As a queer couple, we really wanted to reimagine what the Yoruba engagement could look like in a way that felt authentic to us!" – Tomi + Derin⁠
⁠
The next day, they married in a garden-style wedding surrounded by their family, close friends, and their dog Whiskey. ⁠

Meet Deji Rachel, a talented makeup artist who has spent nearly a decade serving over 400 brides and countless clients worldwide. From her humble beginnings with a few makeup brushes to becoming a judge at The National Wedding Awards and working with industry giants like Chanel 4, Deji’s journey is nothing short of inspiring.

Her story is one of faith, family, passion, and purpose. With a heart for people and a commitment to excellence, she believes that success isn’t just about skills—it’s about character and integrity. Deji’s artistry goes beyond makeup; it’s about making brides feel confident, radiant, and celebrated on their special day.

Congrats are in Order again… not just to the newlyweds but to the blessings this union has given all of us. 

My big bro was my first best friend, 2nd male figure, & one to love me, aggravate me, & call me out on my own  at all times. 

I have seen him grow, through BS, through childhood trauma, even cancer as a teen. 

But one thing this man doesn’t do is give up on anything. 

He is a hard headed man just Iike dad but he loves hard yet still a big teddy bear. 

Bro, I wanna say I am so proud of YOU. Yoooooo you got married before me!!! Got damnit! lol  but nah bro, I’m so happy for yall. Frfr 

You gave me a new sister to build with. One who adores u like none other. The wedding showed me such a powerful fun dynamic in you two, a fun loving, carefree love I only pray for. 

This journey didn’t start perfect, it won’t be perfect, but what I know is both of y’all’s love for each other has stood the test of time and GOD got yall. 

Love you both and congrats again! 

Y’all did that. Shawty we look TF good u hear me!

Subtle glam for the modern day bride ✨ can you guess if I have PARIS Filter On ? 

Bridal makeup these days has evolved to embrace both timeless elegance , classics and with a blend of modern trends.

Here are some common requests of bridal makeup today by most brides. 

A Flawless Natural Glow from within look where Brides today prefer a fresh, dewy complexion that enhances their natural beauty that i try to achieve with intense skin prep with right products customised for my clients 
Soft, Radiant Skin that looks plump and hydrated where they key role is of religious skincare done regularly prior to big day to create a smooth, glowing base that looks like skin. 
Smudged kohl eyes & natural looking eyelashes - many modern brides opt for soft kohl which is my personal fav as well with shimmers & pair of natural looking falsies or individual lashes for that natural finish. 

Nude / Ombré Luscious Lips: Nude, soft pinks, and mauve tones , soft browns are popular , I always ensure to show a vast range of lip options which can make or break a look. 

Airbrush makeup for Long-Lasting base : With the expectation that brides will be emotional, dancing, and eating, makeup today is all about staying in place for the day and sometimes even for back to back events , my most trusted airbrush makeup for the big day especially for an outdoor wedding.

Customisable bridal  Looks: Many brides are choosing makeup that reflects their unique personality—whether it’s minimalistic, glowy, or matte. Get in touch for your big day glam needs.

•Newsreel footage of Harry Belafonte and his second wife, Julie Robinson, taken at the New York City premiere of the Marilyn Monroe film, “Some Like it Hot,” 1959. 

In 1954, Belafonte was working on the Otto Preminger film, “Carmen Jones,” when he was introduced to Julie Robinson, an actress and dancer who was also cast in the film. 

At the time, Belafonte was married to his first wife, Marguerite Byrd, while Robinson was involved with Marlon Brando and while they kept their romance on the down low for a couple of years, by 1956, Belafonte had revealed the affair to his wife and in 1957, he and Byrd officially divorced. 

Just a few weeks later on March 8, 1957, Belafonte married Robinson at a small ceremony in New York City and soon after their nuptials, the newlyweds uprooted to Los Angeles where they would reside for the rest of their marriage. 

On September 30, 1957, the couple welcomed their first child together, David Belafonte, before giving birth to a daughter, Gina, four years later in 1961. 

Throughout the 1960s, both Belafonte and Robinson became active members of the Civil Rights Movement, attending rallies and protests in support of close friend, Martin Luther King Jr. 

In 1963, Belafonte infamously bailed King out of jail following his arrest in Birmingham, Alabama and the two went on to kickstart the March on Washington which took place on August 28, 1963. 

By the 1980s, Belafonte began to focus the majority of his attention towards humanitarian efforts, spearheading events to support AIDS research and raising awareness for Prostate Cancer which he was diagnosed with in 1996. 

By the early 2000s, Belafonte began to feel trapped in his marriage to Robinson and in 2004, the couple divorced after over forty-seven years of marriage.

Following their divorce, Belafonte wed once more to Pamela Frank in 2008 and the couple would enjoy nearly fifteen years together before his death on April 25, 2023 at the age of ninety-six.

Robinson never remarried following her divorce and lived out the remainder of her life in California before passing away on March 9, 2024 at the age of ninety-five.

Llevo una buena semana hablando de libros con mi madre. 

Nos intercambiamos y regalamos con premura, como si en ellos estuviera “eso” que nos falta. 

Ella está ahora viajando a Japón gracias a “Soy un gato” y “El crisantelmo y la espada” y yo acabo de reponorme del “Reencuentro” de Fred Uhlman y he vuelto a La Comarca con Bilbo Bolsón, que siempre me ha hecho feliz. 

Y hoy, Juan José Millás en su columna de @el_pais habla sobre los lugares a los que llegamos dentro de un libro. 

Habla de una chica anónima con la que compartía vagón de Metro. 

“Todos íbamos dentro de un vehículo menos ella, que iba dentro de un libro.”

Elena, la protagonista de las fotos y ese vestido hipnótico, llevó sus alianzas en un libro de Harry Potter. 

“Yo he llegado a todas partes dentro de un libro, pero a veces lo olvido y me empeño en llegar de otros modos” concluye Millás.

Did you know you can get married at Red Rocks? 

The Red Rocks Trading Post is a wedding venue less than 30 minutes from Denver in Colorado.

It’s a perfect outdoor micro wedding venue, but it’s also good for larger weddings as you can also have up to 120 guests for ceremony & reception.

Pricing for ceremony only starts at $1500! If you want a ceremony and reception package they have other options that vary on pricing depending on day of the week, starting around ~$4000+.

VENUE SPOTLIGHT // Borgo del Carato ~ Sicily 

Set on 90 hectares of private parkland, Borgo del Carato is a luxury resort that blends modern design with authentic Sicilian charm. Surrounded by ancient olive and carob trees, it’s a true slice of historic Sicily.

Once a collection of farmers’ and shepherds’ houses it makes the perfect setting for weddings. With a variety of spaces to celebrate such as a saltwater pool, a courtyard and a restored private chapel with original lime plaster, limestone walls and Baroque stone flooring- you’ll be spoilt for choice at this Sicilian gem.

Nearest airports: Catania 1hr 
 Hosts up to 300 guests
 Sleeps up to 65 guests across 27 rooms
 Wet weather option up to 150 people
 Civil ceremony available onsite
 Churches nearby in Palazzolo & Syracuse

#onthisday 12 December 1992

Anne, Princess Royal married Timothy Laurence.

Anne, Princess Royal married Timothy Laurence, then a commander in the Royal Navy, at Crathie Kirk, near Balmoral Castle, on 12 December 1992.

The couple chose to marry in Scotland as the Church of England did not routinely allow divorced persons whose former spouses are still living to remarry in its churches, while the Church of Scotland did under certain circumstances.

In participating in this ceremony, Anne became the first Royal divorcée to remarry since Victoria, Grand Duchess of Hesse & by Rhine, did so in 1905.

Like Phillips* before him, Laurence received no peerage, & the couple leased a flat in Dolphin Square, London.

They later gave up this city home & now reside between an apartment at St James's Palace & Gatcombe Park. Anne has no children by Laurence.

The current title of Laurence is ; Vice Admiral Sir Timothy Laurence.

* The Queen had offered Phillips an earldom on his wedding day, as was customary for untitled men marrying into the Royal Family. However, Phillips did not accept the offer.

#onthisday 20 November 1947

Princess Elizabeth married Philip Mountbatten

  Princess Elizabeth (later Queen Elizabeth II) & Philip Mountbatten (later Prince Philip, Duke of Edinburgh) were married on 20 November 1947 at Westminster Abbey.

Princess Elizabeth was attended by eight bridesmaids: HRH The Princess Margaret (her younger sister), HRH Princess Alexandra of Kent (her first cousin), Lady Caroline Montagu-Douglas-Scott (daughter of the Duke of Buccleuch), Lady Mary Cambridge (her second cousin), Lady Elizabeth Lambart (daughter of the Earl of Cavan), The Hon. Pamela Mountbatten (Philip's first cousin), The Hon. Margaret Elphinstone (her first cousin) & The Hon. Diana Bowes-Lyon (her first cousin). Her cousins Prince William of Gloucester & Prince Michael of Kent served as page boys.

The royal parties were brought in large carriage processions, the first with The Queen & Princess Margaret & later a procession with Queen Mary. At Kensington Palace, Philip departed with his best man, the Marquess of Milford Haven. Princess Elizabeth arrived at the Abbey with her father, King George, in the Irish State Coach.

The wedding ceremony was officiated by the Archbishop of Canterbury, Geoffrey Fisher, & the Archbishop of York, Cyril Garbett. The ceremony was recorded & broadcast by BBC Radio to 200 million people around the world. Elizabeth & Philip then proceeded to Buckingham Palace, where a breakfast was held at the Ball Supper-room. The couple received over 2,500 wedding presents from around the world & around 10,000 telegrams of congratulations.

Upon their marriage, Elizabeth took the title of her husband & became Princess Elizabeth, Duchess of Edinburgh. They departed for their honeymoon in Broadlands in Hampshire, home of Philip's uncle, Earl Mountbatten

Thanks to a growing collective, we continue our “Meet the Artist” series into 2025 with our newest talent, @danitoscanophoto! Known for her thoughtful approach and timeless imagery, Dani is a wedding and portrait photographer who artfully combines film and digital photography. Her unique style blends a photojournalistic sensibility with an editorial eye, capturing candid moments and gently guided portraits that feel organic and beautiful.

Dani’s work is defined by her ability to find beauty in real moments, golden light, and heartfelt connections. She approaches every wedding with an intentional focus on truth and artistry, shaping each image into a stunning piece of art. Recently named a rising star wedding photographer by Rangefinder Magazine, her work has been featured in BRIDES, The Lane, The Friend Club, and more.

When she’s not photographing love stories around the globe, Dani enjoys painting with watercolor, spending time with her husband and pets, soaking up the California sunshine, and hosting intimate gatherings with friends.

HAPPY NEW (CAKE) YEAR
Das neue Jahr hat begonnen, und ich freue mich riesig auf ein süßes 2025 voller neuer Herausforderungen und wunderbarer Party & Wedding Cakes! 
Ich bin so dankbar für all die besonderen Torten, die wir im letzten Jahr rausgeben durften – wie bei dieser wunderschönen Hochzeit, deren Highlight (neben dem Brautpaar natürlich ) diese Torte für mich war. Diese tollen Fotos hat Diana eingefangen – ich finde, es bringt die Magie des Moments einfach perfekt rüber!

Für 2025 habe ich noch Kapazitäten frei und freue mich darauf, eure Traumtorte für euren großen Tag zu zaubern.
Egal ob romantisch, modern oder extravagant – lasst uns zusammen eure Wünsche umsetzen!

Meldet euch über meine Website, um euren Termin zu sichern und eine Cake Tasting Box zu bestellen. Ich kann es kaum erwarten, Teil eures besonderen Tages zu sein.

Auf ein süßes neues Jahr voller Liebe, Kuchen und ganz viel Kreativität!

Absolutely loved working on this gorgeous wedding cake from the weekend! It’s always exciting when couples want something out of the ordinary, and this just screams romantic, chic and playful winter wedding. We went for a moody dark red base with a few deep red anthuriums, contrast from small white orchids, and a playful mix of blackberries, golden berries and satsuma mandarin halves. The bottom tier was Pearadise (cardamom, pear and salted caramel) and the top two were Cherry on Top (chocolate, cherry and vanilla bean).

83 years ago today on January 10, 1942, Mickey Rooney and Ava Gardner exchanged vows in a ceremony that marked their first marriage for them both. 
Ava Gardner was nineteen years old, Mickey Rooney twenty-one. 

At the time, Ava Gardner was still far from famous, having just arrived in Hollywood, but Mickey Rooney was a hugely popular star with a long list of accolades already.

Since both Mickey and Ava were under contract with MGM, they had to have the permission of studio head Louis B. Mayer in order to marry. Mayer was worried about how fans would react if one of his biggest stars, Mickey Rooney, who was especially popular in the “Andy Hardy” movies, was taken off the market.

Ava wore a blue tailored suit with a corsage of Cattaleya orchids rather than a white wedding gown. She said of agreeing to the small wedding: “it ruined my dream of getting married at a beautiful ceremony dressed in a white wedding gown. I didn’t mind missing out on the big wedding, but I did miss the dress.”

After their honeymoon the couple visited Ava’s family while in North Carolina. (Photo 10)

“Mama had made herself pretty. She’d got herself dressed to the nines to meet her famous son-in-law…and the house was filled, which couldn’t have made Mama happier because she loved people around her. And Mickey liked that sort of situation, too, and in my terms gave the greatest and most heartwarming performance of his life. He entertained Mama, he hugged her, he made her laugh, he brought tears to her eyes. He did his impersonations, he did his songs and dances –it was a wonderful, wonderful occasion for Mama, who we all knew was slowly dying. Although I had loved Mickey from the start, that show he put on moved me beyond words.”

The marriage only lasted a year. The divorce was final on May 21, 1943, the same day Ava’s mother passed away.
They remained friendly throughout Ava’s life.

How to handcraft the "Eternal Motion" Diamond Ring?

"Eternal Motion" Diamond Ring

The "Eternal Motion" ring elegantly combines the flow of time with eternal love. The groove design of the ring represents the track of time, while the six evenly spaced gears within the groove are designed to rotate freely, symbolizing the endless flow and change of time. As the gears turn, the diamonds embedded between them sparkle, representing the constant shifts in love and the eternal bond that remains. The diamonds within the gears not only add to the luxurious feel but also symbolize that, even in the flow of time, love remains as brilliant and enduring as the diamonds. This ring, with its precise mechanical design and the radiance of diamonds, conveys the eternal connection between time, mechanics, and love, showcasing a commitment to love and a deep appreciation for beautiful moments.

A Sweet Love Story! ❤️

Amid a global pandemic that had brought the world to a standstill, a simple act of kindness on social media sparked a connection that would forever change our lives. It was a birthday celebration shared virtually through an Instagram post by her bridesmaid. As I scrolled through the well-wishes, one comment caught my eye – a heartfelt birthday greeting from a stranger, yet one that radiated warmth and sincerity. Intrigued, I reached out to this stranger and thus began a conversation that would span weeks and months, transcending the digital realm and forging a bond that grew stronger with each exchange. We shared our hopes, our dreams, and our fears, finding solace in the understanding that we had found a kindred spirit in the midst of a world that seemed to have lost its way. Finally, in November 2020, the stars aligned, and we had the opportunity to meet in person in the vibrant city of Dubai. As our eyes met for the first time, it was as if the world around us had faded away, and all that mattered was the connection we had forged through the depths of our conversations. From that fateful birthday wish, our love blossomed like a desert rose, resilient and beautiful, a testament to the power of serendipity and the enduring strength of the human spirit. And as we stand here today, united in matrimony, we celebrate not only our love but also the incredible journey that brought us together – a journey that began with a simple act of kindness and blossomed into a lifetime of happiness.

As a photographer, some moments leave a lasting imprint on your heart, and this South Indian wedding was one of them. The bride, draped in the finest silk saree with intricate temple jewelry, was the embodiment of grace and beauty—every step she took exuded the timeless elegance of tradition. The groom, on the other hand, was the picture of humility and charm, with a quiet confidence that spoke volumes about his character. Watching them exchange vows amidst the sacred chants and the vibrant hues of a Brahmin wedding was a sight to behold. It wasn't just a union of two souls but a celebration of culture, love, and values that define a perfect South Indian wedding. Capturing these moments felt like freezing a story of devotion and beauty that will be cherished for generations.

Throwback to April and Sebastien’s wedding at Château d’Ermenonville last September.

For April, who usually embraces minimalistic makeup, we created a natural, romantic and timeless bridal look that enhances her features while staying true to her personal aesthetic. 

Thank you April for your trust and your kind words:

Le Domaine du Bijoutier, un lieu d’exception en Provence.
Charme, élégance et authenticité : notre domaine est un écrin parfait pour accueillir vos événements marquants, qu’il s’agisse de mariages, séminaires ou anniversaires.

✨ Un cadre unique et modulable pour vos événements :

Le jardin du vin d’honneur : Ce vaste espace verdoyant est idéal pour partager un moment convivial avec vos invités.

La salle de réception : Spacieuse et élégante, avec ses murs en pierre authentiques qui ajoutent une touche intemporelle, elle peut recevoir 250 convives pour des repas et des soirées mémorables.

Les extérieurs baignés de lumière : Imaginez une cérémonie laïque au cœur de nos champs de lavande, un cadre enchanteur pour immortaliser vos plus beaux moments.

La piscine : Entourée d’un aménagement chic et naturel, elle offre un espace parfait pour des instants de détente ou des photos uniques, surtout au coucher du soleil.

Les coins intimes et chaleureux : Nos murs en pierre se mêlent harmonieusement aux espaces ombragés et aux jardins pour créer une ambiance authentique et pleine de caractère.

✨ Une expérience qui allie authenticité et nature :
Le Domaine du Bijoutier est le mariage parfait entre le charme provençal et l’élégance contemporaine. Les pierres anciennes, les champs de lavande, la piscine et les jardins luxuriants se combinent pour offrir un cadre exceptionnel et intemporel.

 Explorez notre domaine dès maintenant :
Découvrez l’univers unique du domaine en visionnant nos vidéos virtuelles sur notre site internet ou sur mariage.net. 

https://domainedubijoutier.com/

 Contactez-nous pour organiser une visite et imaginer ensemble votre projet.

 Un lieu qui sublimera vos plus beaux moments et marquera les esprits.

The evening reception for Nam Parama and Grid beautifully embodied a modern aesthetic, a style highly celebrated in today’s wedding world. Eschewing rigid geometry, the table arrangements flowed with organic freedom, creating a sense of movement and lightness. Cascading candles, softly draped table linens, and layered textures added warmth and depth, crafting an ambiance that was both intimate and elegant. This thoughtful, playful design approach seamlessly balanced form and function, setting a chic and contemporary tone.

Adding a personal touch, the couple customized the charger plates with their names, used fresh bread as unique place cards, and turned food and fruits into stunning edible centerpieces. In a heartwarming gesture, the bride herself served pasta to her cherished guests, enhancing the atmosphere with a sense of love and closeness. The result was a celebration that blended timeless luxury with cozy, heartfelt moments.

Set against the breathtaking backdrop of the Habita Beach Club, the reception transformed into not just a celebration of love, but also a testament to artful modernity.

"Thanh Ngọc Tương Phùng" signifies the perfect union, where two families come together in a serene green hue, symbolizing hope and happiness. Phi Diep Team masterfully blends traditional and modern styles, featuring a dominant green tone paired with natural wood, soft silk, and luxurious golden accents. The space is highlighted with green-and-white floral arrangements and stylized classic patterns, creating a unique, innovative ceremony while preserving the essence of Vietnamese culture.

Since ancient times, green has been associated with life, hope, freshness, and harmony with nature, while gold represents prosperity, warmth, and glory, linked to power and abundance. The green-and-gold combination in this concept by Phi Diep Wedding & Event Planner embodies a prosperous, joyful, and auspicious beginning for Huệ Ngọc & Bảo Long.

For couples planning a more intimate celebration, this caterpillar style set up is a dream come true! Abbey Farm’s charming rustic beams and cozy space work beautifully with this flowing table arrangement creating a sense of closeness that’s ideal for smaller wedding parties. 

Rather than traditional rows, these interconnecting tables weave through the room, bringing guests together in an elegant, organic way that allows everyone to feel part of the experience. The abundance of candlelight adds warmth and romance, while the delicate florals bring a touch of nature indoors. They are thoughtfully arranged to lead your eye along the captivating snake like flow of the tables. 

The entire space is welcoming, cohesive and effortlessly beautiful. Every guest feels included, every detail feels intentional and every moment becomes unforgettable.

One of my fave parts of our wedding? 2부! ‍♀️
In Korean weddings, 2부 (Second Part) is the fun, casual half of the celebration, kinda like a mini after-party 

While 1부 (First Part) is all about the formal vows and fancy moments, 2부 is where the real party starts—
 We did a duet (yes, we sang the song playing in the background of this post!)
 Played games with our guests
 And, of course, cut the cake!

Not every wedding has it, but I’m so glad we did!  Which vibe do you like better— part 1 or part 2 of our wedding day?

For her Mehndi, we created a vibrant, colorful celebration filled with joy and energy . But when it came to her wedding day, we knew it had to be something truly magical – a grand, romantic vibe featuring her dreamy mirror aisle and lush red florals ✨. The transformation from one event to the next? Let’s just say it was everything she envisioned and more. ✨

Planning multi-day events is all about crafting unique experiences that still feel connected. We pour our heart into every detail to make sure each celebration is as unforgettable as the last. 

 Dreaming of your perfect wedding or multi-day celebration? Let’s make it a reality! Comment below , send us a DM , or share this post with someone who’s ready to plan their dream events. We can’t wait to bring your vision to life! ✨

Trauzeuge sein? Easy… oder etwa nicht?

Hey du! Wenn du als Trauzeuge oder Trauzeugin am Start bist, hast du nicht nur die Ehre, sondern auch richtig was zu tun. Damit der große Tag des Brautpaares perfekt läuft, hab ich ein paar goldene Tipps für dich.

Erstens: Du bist die Anlaufstelle Nummer 1 für alles und jeden. Egal ob ein Gast die Location nicht findet, ein Dienstleister spontan eine Frage hat oder irgendwas schiefgeht – du bist der Fels in der Brandung. Dein Job? Dafür sorgen, dass das Brautpaar nichts von all dem mitkriegt und einfach nur ihren Tag genießen kann.

Zweitens: Behalte das Timing im Auge! Auf Hochzeiten geht die Zeit schneller rum als du gucken kannst. Du bist derjenige, der dafür sorgt, dass der DJ weiß, wann’s losgeht, der Kuchen nicht vergessen wird und der Ablauf rund läuft – ohne Stress, versteht sich.

Drittens: Werde zum Tanzflächen-Motivator! Nach dem Hochzeitstanz zögern die meisten, die Tanzfläche zu stürmen. Hier kommst du ins Spiel: Schnapp dir ein paar Leute und bring die Party ins Rollen. Glaub mir, du bist der Gamechanger!

Außerdem: Pack ein kleines Notfall-Kit ein. Pflaster für die Blasen, Nähzeug für spontane Knopfdramen, Taschentücher für die Freudentränen – das Brautpaar wird dir dafür den Rest ihres Lebens dankbar sein.

Und die Rede? Kein Grund für Nervosität! Halte sie kurz, charmant und witzig. Ziel ist es, die Gäste zum Lachen und das Brautpaar zum Weinen zu bringen – aber nur vor Rührung, natürlich.

Denk dran: Du bist nicht nur irgendwer an diesem Tag. Du bist die rechte Hand des Brautpaares und einer der wichtigsten Menschen auf dieser Hochzeit. Also: bleib entspannt, hab Spaß und mach diesen Tag unvergesslich – für alle!

A Romantic Marquise diamond engagement ring for lovely Nancy!

Story: David and Nancy came in with the recommendation of David's brothers. Nancy knew she wanted a Marquise shaped diamond in a rose gold setting. For the design, she wanted a romantic ring with detailing and was open to my suggestions.

During our initial meeting, I looked at Nancy's hand structure and personal style and asked her a few questions to understand her. Then I sketched a preliminary design on how I envisioned her ring and I suggested finalizing the details after they pick the center marquise diamond.

For our second meeting, I brought in a few marquise shaped diamonds, all within the criteria that we had discussed, for Nancy and David to pick from. Nancy picked out her favorite diamond right away! Then I went over all the details that Nancy wanted to see in her dream ring and I sketched it for her. She loved the design and left it up to David to surprise her.

David wanted to propose around the holidays. I completed the ring and he picked it up without Nancy knowing about it. Later on, he surprised Nancy and proposed to her with her dream ring. 

Thank you Nancy and David for giving me the opportunity to create for you. And thank you to Sean and Alex, Bianca and Michael, for recommending me! Here's to a great start to 2025! #cynthiabrittcustomjewelry

Communicating with your wedding cake maker is key to getting the cake of your dreams. 

Start by discussing your vision, including flavors, design, and any dietary restrictions. 

Provide inspirational photos and be clear about your budget and timeline. 

Ask for their input and expertise to ensure a delicious and stunning creation. 

Regular updates and tastings will ensure everything goes smoothly, leaving you with a beautiful and tasty centerpiece for your special day. Here are a few questions that you can ask
 
 Do you provide a cake stand? 
 What size of slice will each guest get? 
 Can spare tiers be frozen? 
 How will the cake be delivered? 
 Do you offer cake flavor samples? ‌

As a photographer, some moments leave a lasting imprint on your heart, and this South Indian wedding was one of them. The bride, draped in the finest silk saree with intricate temple jewelry, was the embodiment of grace and beauty—every step she took exuded the timeless elegance of tradition. The groom, on the other hand, was the picture of humility and charm, with a quiet confidence that spoke volumes about his character. Watching them exchange vows amidst the sacred chants and the vibrant hues of a Brahmin wedding was a sight to behold. It wasn't just a union of two souls but a celebration of culture, love, and values that define a perfect South Indian wedding. Capturing these moments felt like freezing a story of devotion and beauty that will be cherished for generations.

Dreaming of a romantic Tuscan wedding? Look no further than @villa_catignano, a breathtaking 17th-century estate nestled in the heart of the Chianti Classico winemaking region, just 8 km from Siena. 

 Location: Villa di Catignano is steeped in history, built in the late 17th century by Monsignor Lodovico Sergardi. Its Giardino all’Italiana, frescoed walls, and stunning views of Siena and the rolling Tuscan hills create an enchanting backdrop for your big day. 

 Event Spaces: Whether you envision an outdoor ceremony in the Italian Garden or an intimate reception in the Grey Hall, Villa di Catignano offers endless possibilities. With accommodations for up to 86 guests and event capacity for up to 120, it’s perfect for celebrating love with your nearest and dearest. 

 Exclusive Features:
	•	Elegant accommodations with antique decor and frescoed ceilings
	•	Rustic farmhouse options with private terraces
	•	Swimming pool with panoramic views 

 Tap the link in bio or check out our Stories to see available dates and learn how to book this unforgettable wedding venue!

What's the number one thing you look for when you're searching for the perfect photographer/videographer? Is it price, style, location, personality, etc? If you've been looking for a photographer/videographer you've probably realized that it can be a little overwhelming at times and I'm here to help you in your search with my 5 best tips on finding the perfect duo! 

If you're a photographer you might mention that they should view their portfolio to see if they have the right style, or that cheaper prices can sometimes be a red flag]

1. View an entire wedding gallery/video done by them 
2. Don’t ever book a photographer/videographer without FaceTiming them first
3. Pay attention to their style and make sure they are exactly what you’re wanting
4. Sticking to your budget is important, but just remember you get what you pay for 
5. Ask them about their experience and what value they bring to the table 

I hope these little tips help you with your search. If you'd love to talk more about hiring us as your photo/video duo then fill out our inquiry page in our bio! We have a few available spots to FaceTime within the next week or two! We would love to send you some more information to see if we'd be a great fit!

Calling all florists wanting to deepen their artistic practice of floral design. Come take a 1:1 workshop with me this winter season. I have a few dates available in January and February to schedule a session with me. Comment “WORKSHOP” for an automated link sent to your inbox, or you can visit the education page on my website to book a session with me. 

As a florist who’s been at this for a minute or two, you can’t help but look around and compare yourself to others who are further along the journey.

I love real flowers so much but for this business it’s a much better idea to use artificial ones. 

This is because the arches then only need to be made once and can be rented out again and again, bringing in far more profit than an arch that can just be rented out once.

Imagine this: perfect, pristine blooms that don’t need water, won’t trigger allergies, and can be reused for multiple weddings. 

We’re talking serious cost-effectiveness and zero stress. 

Our faux flower arches always look flawless and always picture-perfect. 

Plus, you get consistent color and shape, no matter what Mother Nature decides to throw at your big day. 

No wilting, no browning edges, no sad, droopy petals - just pure, photogenic floral magic that looks incredible from first look to last dance. 

Trust me, these artificial beauties are the secret weapon for a drop-dead gorgeous event setup and a thriving successful floral arch rental business.

Recently got engaged and in planning mode and don’t know what you want florally?
A floral favourite to consider… 

✨The meadow box✨

Why are they so good? 

1. Imagine walking down the aisle to these stunners framing your path or have a few pulled together to create a stunning floral meadow scene to get married surrounded by. 
2. They are movable and reusable! How can you not love that? We all know weddings are expensive so the more versatile your arrangements are the better. So from ceremony to venue they can be used to decorate the front of your top table, to surround your cake table or to greet your guests as they enter your wedding breakfast.
3. They are a fabulous way to showcase your stunning blooms! They are show stoppers whatever the size. 

All our arrangements are free from floral foam which means they’re sustainable! So you’re not harming the planet

How to get your wedding guests to arrive on time 

1.) Phrasing 

⭐️ On your wedding website or invitations you can say “doors open at 3:15 for a prompt 4pm ceremony” 

2.) Make it fun 

⭐️ Pre ceremony cocktail hour is a great way to get everybody loaded into the space without makeing them wait! 

⭐️ Or work with your photographer for a red carpet style arrivals photo shoot for your early arrival guests! 

3.) Call you culprits ahead of time 

⭐️ You know who is typically late. Call them and say you are planning on beginning on time and you would love to see their face in the crowd. Tell them how much it would mean to you to be on time.

Absolutely loved working on this gorgeous wedding cake from the weekend! It’s always exciting when couples want something out of the ordinary, and this just screams romantic, chic and playful winter wedding. We went for a moody dark red base with a few deep red anthuriums, contrast from small white orchids, and a playful mix of blackberries, golden berries and satsuma mandarin halves. The bottom tier was Pearadise (cardamom, pear and salted caramel) and the top two were Cherry on Top (chocolate, cherry and vanilla bean).

In a world where moments often fade as quickly as they bloom, some artists create magic by preserving memories in the most delicate and timeless ways. Meet Katie with Pressed Petal Co., a creator who transforms the fleeting beauty of flowers into lasting works of art. Specializing in pressed petals and wedding bouquet preservation, Katie breathes new life into cherished blooms, turning them into stunning keepsakes. From handcrafted wall art to intricate framed designs, each piece is a testament to love, celebration, and the natural beauty of flowers. I had the pleasure of interviewing Katie and hearing more about her work. 

See our newest feature to dive into her unique craft and discover how these preserved petals tell stories that last forever.

The Great Indian Wedding Gifts (By Ishani Dash @ishanidash)

Do straight Indian men truly believe they need to be paid, in gifts, cash, clothes, or otherwise, to marry somebody? Unsurprisingly, many do not treat their wives as partners but continue to dismiss her wishes, feelings, and needs – seeing them as trivial or mere ‘wants’. After all, where the foundation of a marriage is not mutual respect, why on earth would a husband suddenly treat his wife any differently after a wedding thrown in his honor?

My only question to all those who continue to threaten, or what they would call strongly request, a woman to show off her parents’ hard-earned money in the form of expensive jewelry and other gifts is: Do you truly believe a marriage built on a foundation of coercion is a marriage at all?

The financial burden of being a bridesmaid, particularly for destination weddings, can be overwhelming. 

While these costs may seem extreme to some, they’re becoming increasingly common, particularly for elaborate destination events. 

In this case, I was unable to attend due to another conflicting wedding. However, even if there was not another wedding, I might have hesitated to attend due to the significant expenses involved.

Choosing to attend a wedding can be a difficult decision, especially when balancing personal financial goals and not wanting to hurt anyone’s feelings. At the end of the day, a true friend should understand and respect your decision, recognizing that declining an invitation doesn’t diminish your support for their love and happiness.

Have you ever experienced making a tough decision like this due to costs associated with being part of a wedding? Let me know.

-Leandra

One of the grandest Indian weddings ever also cost the Billionaire Laxmi Mittal a big fortune. When his daughter Vanisha’s Mittal got married to Amit Bhatia, a banker the whole world talked about the wedding.
The engagement ceremony at the magnificent Palace of Versailles featured a French opera and Moulin Rouge style cancan dancing.
Next was mehndi and Le Bristol was transformed into an exquisite garden with swings and the works. Top mehndi artists specially flown in from India got busy even as Hindi songs blared from huge speakers.
The wedding itself was held at the breathtaking Vaux le Vicomte estate. Over 35 craftsmen were flown in from Mumbai to erect a mandap on a pond in the sprawling gardens of the estate. Elephants made of fibre glass, minarets and a huge reception hall done up in pink were also put up.

Did I mention some of my fave pieces ever went live this week? 
I love this stack - three chunky antiques and the vintage hall of mirrors linear baguette band. 
These were all found in France and are pretty amazing in terms of quality, uniqueness and on trend. 
The five stone and seven stone are both closed back and both antique but fabricated 100 years apart (the seven stone is Georgian period early 1800s the five stone is very early 1900s). But I am impressed by their brightness as seen in the stack compared to the other two pieces which are open backed. As you can see the closed and foil backed settings are full of life, sparkly and reflective, stacking perfectly with open backed settings. 
✨The Georgian seven stone is at least 3 carats and has a domed back with amazing high crowns to the stones, like cups or bowls of chunky goodness heaping over. 
✨The wide band above it is hefty - 20 grams and 1.5 carats of old mine cuts in 18k gold. 
✨ The five stone low profile band is 3.3 carats and the perfect stacker in an uncommon bezel setting. 
✨ And then at the top we have the 1.2 carat baguette six stone platform band with nearly perfect stones - G/H in color and VVS crystal clear. 
✨ and then swipe to see the daisy cluster ring which has a delicious eye clean pale yellow center and a unique mix of hand cut diamonds (some uncommon cuts) totaling 1.75 carat. 
These along with the ruby and diamond giardinetti bracelet were the highlights of my week! 
Hope everyone is having a beautiful holidays!

Storied Goods Espresso Martini 

Add 1 or 2 SG Cinnamon-Vanilla Sugar Cubes to 1 oz of hot espresso or very strong coffee, and stir to dissolve Cubes. 

Add espresso mixture, 2 oz vodka, 1/2 oz coffee liqueur, like St. George Nola Coffee Liqueur, and ice to cocktail shaker, and shake until well chilled. 

Pour into @estellecoloredglass martini glass, and garnish with coffee beans. 

Warning ⛔️ 
This cocktail is ONLY delicious on the following Days…
Hump Day 
Valentine’s Day ❤️
Galentine’s Day 
Snow Day ❄️
Ice Day 
12 Degrees Day 
Days Ending In Y ‍♀️

Cheers to you and winter! ❄️

Fondée en 2022 par Nicolas et Jessica, parents de trois merveilleux enfants, Jour J Events est le fruit d’une passion commune pour la création d’émotions inoubliables.

Forts de notre formation en tant que Wedding Planners en 2021, nous avons décidé de concrétiser notre vision et de faire briller les yeux de nos clients à travers plus de 150 événements passés.

Chez Jour J Events, chaque projet est unique, car chaque personne l’est aussi. 
Nous nous engageons à réaliser vos projets les plus fous avec professionnalisme et créativité. 

En tant que : 
▪︎ Organisateurs de mariages 
▪︎ Organisateurs et décorateurs d'événements privés et professionnels 
▪︎ Decor de ballon plus communément appelé Balloon Designer,

nous sommes là pour transformer vos idées en réalité.

Founded on a passion for creating exceptional celebrations, ROAM Events is a full-service luxury event planning and design company specializing in weddings, social gatherings, and corporate events. With over a decade of experience crafting sophisticated and personalized experiences, ROAM Events combines flawless execution with unparalleled creativity.

Whether it’s an elegant wedding in Baltimore’s historic venues, a lavish celebration in South Florida, or a destination event anywhere in the world, ROAM Events brings a refined and bespoke approach to every detail. From meticulous planning and vendor coordination to custom design and guest experience management, the team ensures that every event is a seamless, stress-free masterpiece.

Led by Rachael Avara, a seasoned event producer with a background in designing hundreds of high-end events across the U.S., ROAM Events takes pride in crafting unforgettable memories for discerning clients. With a focus on timeless elegance and a commitment to excellence, ROAM Events creates experiences that are as unique as the people they are designed for.

As the year 2024 comes to a close, we at Mitheo Events celebrate and honor the trust our couples have placed in us to bring their dream destination weddings to life across Europe. We cherish our couples, their families, and the unique stories that make every celebration extraordinary.

Eve & Alex’s dream wedding at the iconic Villa Balbiano on Lake Como, Italy, was nothing short of bliss. Their wedding video is destined to be recognized as The World’s Best Wedding Video in 2024, serving as a powerful inspiration that symbolizes resilience, strength, and the profound beauty of life’s triumphs.

@eve.hd told us that her ultimate moment was the moment when she would walk down the aisle by herself to Alex – we created for her a 9 meter barre support dressed with greenery to harmonically blend the natural landscape, accompanied by voluminous aisle flower bushes as per the bride’s vision.

It was an incredibly emotional moment for all of us to witness the strength and determination of our beautiful bride, Eve, as she made her way down the aisle to the love of her life, even on a rainy day in Lake Como, with such grace and resilience.

@michaelatheodor , our founder, had the honor of officiating this extraordinary gathering, where we bore witness to the genuine love story of Eve and Alex—a union defined by their inherent grace, profound beauty, and unwavering strength. 
We are beyond grateful to have been part of their special day and to have shared in their joy.

RAINY DAY PHOTOS! What if it rains on your wedding day? The first thing to remember is to let go of weather expectations and enjoy the day. You and your guests will still have an AMAZING time! Everyone is there for you and for the craic :) Well, also food, drink and a party :) Second - when you choose your venue, make sure you are happy with the indoor spaces - are they cosy, is there clear space or extra room where we can do family & group photos? If it’s absolutely lashing and you don’t want to go outside - are there spaces and rooms where you can imagine your couple’s photos? Windows & windowsills, statement rooms & furniture, staircases and doorframes make for good spots. More often than not it’s not raining heavily all day. If the rain is light, we can still go outside with 2 white umbrellas to capture gardens or the venue setting. Prepare these in advance in the style that you like (make sure there are no logos). For the brides - make sure to have a change of shoes if you want to go outside, so your main shoes don’t get wet. And more importantly - have fun! I love real flowers so much but for this business it’s a much better idea to use artificial ones. 

This is because the arches then only need to be made once and can be rented out again and again, bringing in far more profit than an arch that can just be rented out once.

Imagine this: perfect, pristine blooms that don’t need water, won’t trigger allergies, and can be reused for multiple weddings. 

We’re talking serious cost-effectiveness and zero stress. 

Our faux flower arches always look flawless and always picture-perfect. 

Plus, you get consistent color and shape, no matter what Mother Nature decides to throw at your big day. 

No wilting, no browning edges, no sad, droopy petals - just pure, photogenic floral magic that looks incredible from first look to last dance. 

Trust me, these artificial beauties are the secret weapon for a drop-dead gorgeous event setup and a thriving successful floral arch rental business.

My Journey from Scratch to Success!

I’m overwhelmed with gratitude reflecting on my journey. From humble beginnings to where I am today, it’s been an incredible ride!

I started with NOTHING, but a passion and determination to learn. I invested time and effort into courses, training, and practice. And slowly but surely, my skills improved, and my confidence grew!

Today, I’m proud of what I’ve achieved, and I’m grateful for every step of the journey. The late nights, early mornings, and countless hours of practice have been worth it!

If you’re just starting out or feeling stuck, know that your journey is unique, and progress may be slow, but it’s possible! Keep pushing, learning, and believing in yourself!

I’ll say it once and then let’s just crack on shall we? HAPPY NEW YEAR FLOWER FRIENDS 
A warm welcome to my new followers who’ve joined me here since December, you’re so welcome and Hola lovely followers of old - I hope you’re all well 

It’s Monday and I’m back in the office. I’m not firing on all cylinders - if you read my substack post yesterday I’m recovering from flu but undefeated, I managed to deliver my first job on Saturday in spite of illness, muscles literally running on empty I hauled myself into work mode - the show must go on - and so it did. Yesterday I couldn’t do anything mind!! 

Not one for resolutions, manifestations, manifestos or any of that new year new you stuff. Can’t be doing with it. I’m here, I’m in the office and you know what? It’s bloody GREAT TO BE BACK ! 
Inbox is full of new enquiries  I Love the prospect of new couples, new possibilities, combinations, new ideas and just doing what I do. The FLOWERS.  Further more we’ve got spring to look forward to - first up the hellebores came early and the spring bulbs have broken  soil. I must confess to having a bulb watch obsession - does anyone else check on their bulbs daily? Maybe I’m just weird?! 

I’m replying as fast as I can to my emails and I’m happy to be back in the office, the OPEN sign is virtually switched on and the door wedged open so come on in. 

Here’s to another year round the sun, my 24th as a florist. I’ve a 2025 diary full of gorgeous weddings (and space for more) I’m booking primarily 2025 but yes, I’m feverishly booking 2026 couples in too. So if you’re looking for a florist - get in touch. I’m here for you 

To those who just love the banter and commentary, I’m over on Substack and I’m going to be writing lots more over there going forward. Writing is a joy for me - I love sharing my thoughts as much as doing the flowers so come join me - I promise it’ll be a new adventure together. 
Meantime - this photo sums up that fresh clean feeling you get once you’ve taken out the tree and replaced with spring flowers. 
Let’s get this show on the road …

SALAKOT : is a cone shaped head wear made of bamboo or ratan worn by fishermen and farmers in the rural parts of the country used for protection from the sun during warm work days.

BILAO : is a shallow sieving tool used to wannow rice grains of its dust but is now more used to display food or hold dishes when serving big family portions of it! 

This arch is meant to mimic a stacked sculpture of bilaos and salakots often seen sold on carts pulled by some farm animal like a Kalabaw or a cow through rural towns. These ratan and bamboo pieces are definitely a staple piece in Filipino gatherings and am so happy to have put this together for my cousin’s wedding day and my final wedding for the year!!!

before warren’s first look with cat, he had to prove his love the traditional way—with door games! with challenges set up by the bridesmaids, there was plenty of laughter, negotiations, and some very memorable moments before he finally earned his way to see his bride.

from their sweet first look to their stunning celebration at @citywineryhvweddings, every part of their day was filled with love, fun, and so much personality.

warren and cat’s day wouldn’t have been the same without such an incredible team of vendors bringing everything together. their celebration at @citywineryhvweddings was perfectly coordinated by @gracekellyevents, who made sure every detail ran smoothly. @oneflowerbyl created the most stunning florals to complement the romantic vibe of the day, while cat’s gorgeous @kellyfaetanini dress and warren’s sleek @blacklapel suit added the perfect touch of elegance. the bridesmaids looked amazing in @azazieofficial, and the groomsmen were sharp in @indochinoweddings. @vickyc5ny brought her talent to create flawless beauty looks, and @calculatedconfections provided a beautiful (and delicious!) cake to sweeten the celebration. @silverarrowband kept the energy alive all night, making sure the dance floor was packed and the vibes were perfect. it was truly a team effort to bring cat & warren’s vision to life!

It’s not a party without a good dessert table. Did you know that both bakers and florists can place your cake floral? Some bakers prefer to do it themselves, others love for the florist to jump in with the design. I typically recommend asking your bakery what their preference is first since the cake is their work of art and determine from there who will be adding the floral accents. 
These gorgeous cakes were from HEB and I was lucky enough to go all out on our floral decor. @eliza___anne could not have picked a more perfect cake design and coloring to go with our floral palette.

Christmas season is my favorite time of year. It’s the time of year where love, kindness and a bit of magic seem most evident throughout our communities. I’ve been called naive but really I’m just an optimist when it comes to how the world operates and more specifically how people should treat one another. I think this is part of why weddings are so special to me. So much love and joy and kindness being shared by so many people, what more could we hope for in our daily lives? 
May love, joy and kindness surround you and yours this holiday season.

Photographer @ushnakhanphotography captured every moment with grace, bringing their love to life through her lens. From the carefully chosen venue to the saxophone serenade and a diverse team of Hair & makeup artists, every detail came together in perfect harmony, creating a timeless celebration of love.

Auch wenn man es sich so sehr wünscht, ist gutes Wetter keine Garantier an eurem Hochzeitstag. Genau aus diesem Grund gibt es einige Punkte, die man beachten muss. 

- Ihr macht euch keine Gedanken, ob eure Location eine überdachte Ausweichmöglichkeit hat, oder die Trauung im Innenbereich stattfinden kann. An eurem großen Tag stellt ihr dann leider fest, dass die Location keine Ausweichmöglichkeit bietet und die Trauung fällt sprichwörtlich ins Wasser. 

-  Eure Location hat eine Ausweichmöglichkeit im Innenbereich, diese ist allerdings viel zu klein um alle Gäste für die Trauung unterzubringen und was nun? 
Besprecht genau, wie ihr im Vorfeld mit dieser Situation umgehen würdet oder ob diese Location dann überhaupt in Frage kommt. 

- Die Trauwiese eurer Location ist unglaublich schön, genau richtig für die perfekte Hochzeit. Die überdachte Alternative gleicht eher einem Schuppen und lässt keinerlei freudige Stimmung zu. Ihr denkt euch, an unserer Hochzeit wird das Wetter schon passen und müsst feststellen, dass Wetter ist durchgängig schlecht und es wird eine Schuppenhochzeit und keine Traumhochzeit. 

Achtet unbedingt vor der Auswahl eurer Location, dass alle Faktoren passen und ihr egal wie, den schönsten Tag eures Lebens feiern könnt.

6 TIPPS FÜR DEINE LOCATIONSUCHE 

Jede*r will sie, DIE EINE Location, die kaum ein* andere*r kennt. Die ganz besonders ist. Super Abwechslungsreich, keine Genehmigung erfordert, wo man nicht gestört wird & ganz in Ruhe mit seinen Kund*innen fotografieren kann und wo man geiles Licht hat. 

Wollen wir alle. Mag sein, dass man über sowas mal mit Glück stolpert oder der/die Kund*in einen entsprechenden Ort kennt. Aber in den meisten Fällen bedeutet Locationsuche ARBEIT. Zeitaufwand zum raussuchen, zum hin fahren, planen für Test-Shootings, bearbeiten dieser Test Bilder für Werbung und vor dem nächsten Shooting kurz vorher nochmal abchecken, ob auch in der Zwischenzeit nichts gesperrt oder zerstört wurde. Die Spritkosten nicht zu vergessen. 

Ja, das kann STUNDEN in Anspruch nehmen. Was der Grund dafür ist, dass wir Fotograf*innen auf “Wo ist das?” (Bestenfalls ohne hallo, ohne danke, ohne dass man einem folgt und supportet), sehr allergisch reagieren. Kleiner Tipp: mach das nicht.  Außerdem, wie viel cooler ist es, eigene geile Orte zu erkunden, die sonst niemand kennt und dort einzigartige Bilder zu machen? 

Deswegen gibts hier ein paar Tipps, wie du coole Orte finden kannst und wie du dir deine liebsten Orte und potentielle Locations sortiert abspeichern kannst. Was ist dein bester Tipp für die Locationsuche? Schreib’s uns in die Kommentare. ✨

Disclaimer: Ich sag nicht, dass man sich nicht gegenseitig Supporten und solche Infos nicht rausgeben sollte. Ich will nur aufzeigen, warum man es nicht “einfach so” macht, wenn man sonst von dieser Person nicht wirklich etwas zurück bekommt und das Risiko eingeht, dass beim nächsten mal noch 4 weitere Leute da fotografieren und man mit seinen Kund*innnen dann blöd da steht.

Die perfekte Location für eure Hochzeit finden: 5 Tipps! 

Die Wahl der Hochzeitslocation ist einer der wichtigsten Schritte bei der Planung eures großen Tages. Hier sind 5 Dinge, auf die ihr unbedingt achten solltet:

1. Größe & Kapazität: Stellt sicher, dass die Location ausreichend Platz für eure Gäste bietet. Nicht zu eng, aber auch nicht zu groß – die richtige Balance ist entscheidend!
2. Ambiente & Stil: Wählt eine Location, die zu eurem Hochzeitsstil passt. Ob romantisch, rustikal oder modern – die Location sollte eure Persönlichkeit widerspiegeln.
3. Lage & Erreichbarkeit: Achtet darauf, dass die Location gut erreichbar ist, besonders für Gäste, die von weiter weg anreisen. Überlegt auch, ob Übernachtungsmöglichkeiten in der Nähe vorhanden sind.
4. Budget: Behaltet euer Budget im Blick. Die Location ist oft ein großer Kostenpunkt, daher ist es wichtig, genau zu kalkulieren und versteckte Kosten zu vermeiden.
5. Wetteroptionen: Besonders bei einer Sommerhochzeit ist es wichtig, eine Location zu wählen, die auch bei schlechtem Wetter Alternativen bietet. Ein Plan B ist immer eine gute Idee!

Mit diesen Tipps findet ihr garantiert die perfekte Location für euren unvergesslichen Tag!

SO FINDE ICH DIE BESTEN LOCATIONS  [Werbung, da Seitenmarkierungen]
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Für meine Shootings habe ich mittlerweile eine genaue Vorgehensweise entwickelt, damit ich in einer fremden Stadt einen genauen Plan habe und ohne Stress mein Pensum schaffe  Heute teile ich meine Tipps mit euch  Speichert euch den Post gerne ab ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1. Location scouting
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Bevor ich in eine andere Stadt fahre mache ich mich immer auf Instagram und Pinterest schlau, welche Locations es dort so gibt. Natürlich kann man auch einfach spazieren gehen und auf dem Weg tolle Ecken entdecken, aber das ist für mich nur ein Bonus, ich überlasse da nichts dem Zufall ‼️ Sucht nach dem Ort, nach Hashtags oder bei Inspo Seiten nach inspiration für eure Fotos. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
2. Outfits vorbereiten
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Nachdem die Locations feststehen geht es weiter mit dem raussuchen der Outfits. Ich nehme meist ein paar mehr mit (lieber zu viel als zu wenig).
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ Zu den Farben: Bei bereits bunten Locations setze ich auf schlichte Outfits (schwarz, weiß, grau) und bei eher tristen oder eintönigen gebe ich gerne etwas Kontrast mit knalligeren Farben ♥️ Aber das ist nur meine Strategie, ihr könnt das natürlich so machen wie ihr wollt. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ Für Fotos eignen sich jedoch eher auffällige Outfits (zum Beispiel mein gepunkteter Jumpsuit - der ist in echt aber auch auf Fotos ein absoluter Hingucker). Überlegt euch auch worin ihr euch wohl fühlt. Wenn ihr euch nicht wohl in eurem Outfit fühlt, dann wird man es auf den Fotos sehen und das bringt dann keinem was.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
3. Entspannte Stimmung für das Shooting schaffen
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Mittlerweile stelle ich mich auch vor vielen Leuten hin und mache meine Fotos, wenn es nicht anders geht. ABER im Idealfall stehe ich sehr früh auf, mache mich fertig und gehe zum Shooting. Ich mag es nicht, wenn viele Leute in Hintergrund sind, das zerstört meiner Meinung nach ein Bild! Deshalb versuche ich so früh es geht an den Locations zu sein  Je früher desto besser. Ich bin dann auch viel besser drauf, weil ich weis ich habe danach den ganzen Tag „frei“ #torismicommunity

✨ Unvergessliche Momente im „Destillenzi“ am Tegernsee ✨
Träumst du von einer Hochzeit, die sowohl romantisch als auch unvergesslich ist? Der Veranstaltungsraum „Destillenzi“ bietet dir genau das! 

 Der perfekte Rahmen für deinen schönsten Tag 
Ob intime Feier im kleinen Kreis oder ein rauschendes Fest mit bis zu 80 Gästen – im „Destillenzi“ wird jede Hochzeit zu einem unvergesslichen Erlebnis. Umgeben von viel hellem Holz und einer liebevollen Einrichtung, spürst du die gemütliche bayerische Lebensart in jeder Ecke.

 Die Alpen als beeindruckende Kulisse 
Stell dir vor, wie du auf der großen Terrasse stehst, den Blick auf die majestätische Alpenkulisse gerichtet. Dieses Panorama ist nicht nur atemberaubend, sondern auch der perfekte Hintergrund für deine Hochzeitsfotos. Deine Gäste werden diesen Moment nie vergessen!

 Moderne Ausstattung und Feiern bis zum Morgengrauen 
Das „Destillenzi“ ist mit allem ausgestattet, was du für eine unvergessliche Feier brauchst: WLAN, Großbildfernseher, Mikrofon und eine Musikanlage für drinnen und draußen. Feiere bis die ersten Sonnenstrahlen den Tegernsee erleuchten!

 Freie Trauung im Grünen

Gestern war ich nach der Arbeit mit @frenchiefayne auf Krokusjagd.  Wir sind 45 min zu einem Park gefahren, in dem 50000 Krokusse gepflanzt sein sollten. Großzügig gerechnet waren es dann etwa 50.   Wir haben dann noch einen anderen Ort dort gesucht, für den wir erst mal recherchieren mussten, wo die Statur im Bildhintergrund steht ️, aber auch da nur ein paar armselige Krokusse.(siehe Story) Insgesamt war das eine Aktion von 4 Stunden, die quasi nix gebracht hat.  Auf dem Rückweg sind wir aber noch spontan bei einem anderen Park vorbei, den wir bei unserer Recherche gefunden haben, und dort waren tatsächlich Krokusse.  Es war aber schon zu dunkel, daher müssen wir nochmal los.  Ich wollte das einfach mal erzählen, weil viele Leute gar nicht wissen, dass oft Detektivarbeit, Zeit und Sprittgeld hinter den Bildern stecken und man über die tollen Orte nicht von selbst stolpert. Uns macht das Spaß, weils ein bisschen wie ne Schatzsuche ist und man kann halt nicht immer auf Gold stoßen.  Aber ich bekomm Bluthochdruck, wenn mir dann Leute einfach nur schreiben "wo ist das?" Ohne hallo, bitte oder danke.  Mal im Ernst, im richtigen Leben würde ich die Straßenseite wechseln, wenn mich einer so von der Seite anlabert.  Wer nett fragt oder sich auch sonst für unseren Account interessiert, dem sag ich das gerne (solange der Ort das abkann) . Ich bin da echt nicht so, aber wer sogar zu faul ist, die Frage wenigstens nett zu verpacken, der hat sich dann einfach nicht für die Geheiminfos qualifiziert. 
~

BALANCEAKT GASTGEBER & HOCHZEITSPAAR.⁠
⁠
Oh, wie ich das Feiern und beisammen sein mit den Liebsten liebe. Da ist diese schöne, kribbelige Vorfreude. Das sorgfältige Zusammenstellen aller Bestandteile, die das Fest besonders machen. Speisen und Getränke werden ausgewählt. Der Tisch festlich dekoriert und das passende Outfit zurechtgelegt. Zahlreiche kleine Details, bis alles perfekt ist und die Gäste kommen. ⁠
Dann heißt es den Twist, zwischen Koch, Entertainer, Kümmerer....hinbekommen. Dabei aber eben auch gelöst den Abend zu genießen. Was bei kleineren Festen mit Freunden und Familie einen schon manchmal vor die eine oder andere Herausforderung stellt, ist bei größeren oder aufwendigen Festen wie der Hochzeit eine nahezu unlösbare Aufgabe. ⁠
Doch dafür gibt es ja zum Glück eine optimale Lösung!
Wenn ihr noch am überlegen seid oder Euch über die Möglichkeiten der Unterstützung bei der Planung und Durchführung Eurer Hochzeit informieren wollt, dann vereinbart gerne ein unverbindliches Kennenlerngespräch. Lasst uns herausfinden, wie ich Euch bei der Verwirklichung Eures Fest der Liebe unterstützen kann. ⁠

Blue hour, golden cliffs, and a beach all to ourselves—does it get any more dreamy? ✨ This engagement session was everything I could have hoped for: quiet waves, soft light, and K&A so full of love they made the whole world fade away.

One of my favorite parts of being a photographer is helping every couple find their perfect photo location. Whether it’s a hidden beach, a forest trail, or a sunlit field, I work with you to find the best locations—taking into account weather, crowds, and all the little details—so you can relax, be present, and just enjoy the moment together.

WE’RE ENGAGED (Read below for the engagement story) 
So as most of you know I’ve wanted to create cute couple photos of Kory and I to use for a post to share our backstory on how we met. So this past weekend we planned to do just that...but Kory had something else planned. So we headed to the beach for a relaxing three day weekend. One of the days we planned to go to Cape Lookout (I’ve been wanting to go there forever). Before we got there Kory said he had a great idea for one of the couple photos....he said why don’t you spin around towards me and act surprised at the Conch shell he had found (Cape Lookout is known for its Conch Shells). I personally didn’t think this idea would work but I figured let’s give it a try. So as you can hear in the video...if you watch it with sound you will hear me say I don’t think this is gonna work and then as Kory is trying to get ready to propose I’m over there trying to practice my spin lmao. Finally when I spun around there he was on his knee with a gorgeous ring in his hand. In that moment I was completely shocked and filled with so many emotions. I’ve always dreamed of him doing this and it was actually happening!! I’m so insanely excited to be your wife Kory and officially become a Purks!! I love you so much and can’t wait to spend the rest of my life with you!! #koryandemily
