I’m revisiting some of my 2024 bouquets and will talk you through some of the details which I feel made these flowers so uniquely memorable. 
First up this elopement bouquet for Harriette and Pav who were marrying at an intimate family ceremony in London. 
This is an homage to pink - from the hottest cerise to the prettiest palest blush pink and the timeframe the end of April when the tulips are out-out! 

Scroll left and you’ll note our bride Harriette had the most gorgeous pair of hot pink heels which she wanted to pick up in her bouquet. 

I’m a big fan of colour and this bouquet was a joyful reflection of the season in which it was made, 99% locally grown blooms and a rare occasion when my own home grown tulips played a leading role in the recipe. I recessed white azaleas which created a frilly froth in lieu of foliage alongside those epic ranunculus and anemones… 

The flowers bounced around and squeaked (as only tulips can)! I loved this particular combination more than I can say.  When using local seasonal flowers - one cannot guarantee anything, it’s often pot luck and yet these make the most memorable arrangements IMHO. 
So when I’m in conversation with couples - I often emphasise the importance of their putting ALL of their trust in me, allowing me to understand what it is they’re hoping to have and yet allowing me to work with whatever is available at that precise moment. No two years are ever the same and I think my work is richer and more beautiful for that serendipity. 
Unscripted seasonality makes the most beautiful bouquets and arrangements and the results are one off showstoppers such as this. 

With thanks to @little_acorn_silks for the hot pink velvet ribbon and @marlston_farmgirl  for those glorious ranunculus and anemones which I believe continued to flower into May last year. 

The only imported addition were the butterfly ranunculus, Bombastic spray roses & peony - thank you @hoekflowers !

A statement floral installation not only brings drama and beauty to your event, but also offers incredible value for money. Instead of allocating your budget across multiple smaller arrangements that may blend into the background, investing in one striking, large-scale piece creates a focal point that leaves a lasting impression. 

Statement designs have the power to transform a space, drawing attention and elevating the overall atmosphere, whether it’s a grand archway, cascading staircase or dramatic fireplace installation. These impactful arrangements not only photograph beautifully but also become a memorable centrepiece that your guests will talk about long after the event. By focusing on one standout feature you can achieve a cohesive aesthetic without stretching your budget too thinly.

One of the biggest disaster scenarios that keeps me up at night is how to manage my business as a one woman show in the event of an emergency. I’ve always liked to think I have everything under control but this particular wedding it was actually put to the test when I went into labor two weeks early just a couple days before the wedding. 

Thanks to careful planning, ordering & recipe planning, and a team of dependable freelancers, everything went off without a hitch! Plus I was home in time to quickly pop into the studio to make the bridal bouquet the morning of the wedding before the team loaded up for the venue. 

Many thanks again @fleurconnecticut & @brittany_deeprootedllc !

most times when people ask why we take pictures of shoes and bags and all. i often say that “the typical couple spends a fortune on their personal effects (shoes, bags, jewelry, and other accessories). On the wedding day, these items might not even get a second look especially with the rush of the day. (Think of how many bride’s earrings or necklaces or shoes you have noticed in the last couple of weddings you attended. My best guess is none). But for us as photographers, they’re more than just accessories, they’re part of the story. By capturing these details, we magnify their beauty and significance. When couples look through their albums, they relive the positive results of their styling decisions.
Shoutout to able photographers that go the extra mile to give their best.

•Alice Faye and her husband, Phil Harris, are photographed together for their radio program, “The Phil Harris-Alice Faye Show,” 1950. 

In 1940, Faye was already a beloved film star, then recently divorced from her first husband, Tony Martin, when she decided to try her hand on the radio. 

During an appearance on Rudy Vallee’s program, The Fleischmann Hour, in 1941, Faye was introduced to Phil Harris, an orchestra leader who she felt instantly drawn to. 

Soon after their introduction, the two began dating and just a few months later on May 12, 1941, the couple married at a courthouse ceremony in Juarez, Mexico.

Soon after their nuptials, the newlyweds held a more lavish ceremony in California for their friends and family and it was during this time that Faye became pregnant, giving birth to their first child, Alice Jr., in 1942. Two years later on April 22, 1944, the couple welcomed a second child who they named Phyllis.

Following the births of their children, Faye decided to permanently step away from the silver screen in favor of becoming a radio talk show host. 

In 1948, Faye teamed up with her husband to make, “The Phil Harris-Alice Faye Show,” and over the next few years, the two would cement their legacy in comedy after teaming up with Jack Benny on his famous radio series, “The Jack Benny Program.”

Following the shows end in 1965, Faye and Harris began to withdraw from Hollywood with the actors only making sporadic appearances on both radio and television over the coming years. 

Faye and Harris went on to remain happily married for over fifty years before Harris’ death on August 11, 1995 at the age of ninety-one.

Alice went on to outlive her husband by only three years, passing away in 1998 at the age of eighty-three.

Today, the couple are buried alongside one another at Forest Lawn Cemetery in California.

How to Eat at Weddings  (Read Carefully)

Step 1: Walk in. Admire the decor. Spot the food counters.
Step 2: Grab a plate. Eat. Enjoy every bite. Don’t count calories.
Step 3: Repeat Step 2. (Because gulab jamun doesn’t track itself, and neither should you today.)
Step 4: Laugh, dance, make memories. Fitness is a lifestyle, but so is celebrating life.

Too many people stress over every meal, forgetting that food is also about culture, love, and joy. One meal won’t ruin your progress, but an unhealthy obsession with perfection will. So when it’s time to feast, FEAST.

Enjoy the wedding. Enjoy the vacation. Enjoy life. The gym will always be there, and so will I to help you get back on track!

 Drop a ❤️ if you agree!

My wedding dress before and after…read below 

Deciding to open up my wedding dress after it had been preserved for 10 years was something I never thought I’d do. With our 10th wedding anniversary party coming up I wanted to wear something special. That’s when I got to thinking about wearing my dress again. 

Even just getting the box out of the closet had my heart racing! The preservation box was inside another box, and every step of unboxing felt like opening a time capsule. When I finally saw my dress again, it was like seeing it for the very first time. I had completely forgotten about the stunning beading on the bodice. 

Getting the dress out of that gold box was not easy. It was strapped in tight, leaving no room for it to move! When I finally held it in my hands, I remembered just how heavy it was—a detail I’d completely forgotten over the years. Fun fact: my seamstress actually sewed a belt inside the dress to help support its weight!

Trying it on was a whole other adventure. I couldn’t zip it up myself (another thing I forgot—you need at least one, if not two people, to zip it up!). 

When it came to deciding what to do with the dress, I knew I wanted to overall keep it the same. I decided to have the ball gown skirt chopped off and transform it into a chic mini dress. I wasn’t sure how it would look with the heavier satin fabric, but my alteration expert assured me it could be done. After dropping it off, I couldn’t wait to see the result.

A week later, I went back to see the “rough draft,” and it was absolutely perfect. My dress had gone from a big ball gown to an elegant mini dress. I was so excited to surprise Cody and everyone else at our 10th wedding anniversary party.

Looking back, I’m so happy I preserved my dress and chose to give it a new purpose for such a special milestone. It felt like the perfect way to celebrate a decade of marriage—something old, reimagined into something new.

 Here’s your PSA: if you’ve preserved your wedding dress, don’t be afraid to open that box! It’s such a fun and sentimental experience, and you just might find a way to breathe new life into it for another unforgettable moment.

J‘avais tellement hâte de partager avec vous ma papeterie de mariage, co-créée avec l’atelier français @cottonbirdfr ️

Cotton Bird a créé avec moi une papeterie sur-mesure qui reflète mon univers et cette ambiance hivernale que j’aime tant. Un faire-part délicatement orné d’un calque inspiré de la toile de Jouy, des illustrations de personnages et décors rappelant l’élégance de l’époque de la Régence, et des détails dorés, comme un médaillon symbolisant l’union du mariage.

Le thème du faire-part se décline sur une multitude de produits : il est possible de créer toute la décoration du mariage pour qu’elle soit assortie à votre faire-part : menu, marque-places, livrets de cérémonie panneaux de mariage, cartes pour l’urne, bougies, boîtes à biscuits, cornets à pétales et bien plus encore… Tout est pensé pour créer une atmosphère magique et unique, à l’image du plus beau jour de ma vie.

Timeless Fonts to Elevate Your Wedding Stationery ✨

Your wedding stationery sets the tone for your big day, and choosing the right font can make all the difference. These four stunning fonts strike the perfect balance between chic and effortless, ensuring your designs stand out while staying timeless.

If you love these, comment ‘Fonts’ and I’ll send you the link to them  

 Lucy Rose
A modern serif with soft curves and elegant details. It’s perfect for creating a romantic yet contemporary feel, ideal for invitations or menus.

 Cinzel
Inspired by classical Roman inscriptions, this bold, sophisticated serif is all about timeless elegance. Use it for headings or signage to make a statement.

 Dream Avenue
This whimsical script font feels light and graceful, like a handwritten note. It’s perfect for adding a personal, intimate touch to your stationery.

 Coldiac
A luxe serif with strong lines and a hint of vintage charm. It’s the go-to for creating high-end, polished designs with a classic edge.

Pair these fonts with thoughtful design, and your wedding stationery will exude style and sophistication. Which one’s your favourite?

4 Dreamy Fonts for a Romantic Wedding ✨

Choosing the perfect wedding font is just as important as picking your colour palette or floral arrangements—it sets the tone for your big day! If you’re planning a romantic wedding, these four elegant fonts will add the perfect touch of charm and sophistication to your wedding invitations, signage, and stationery. 

 Blosta – A timeless calligraphy-style font, perfect for classic and elegant wedding invitations

 Tan Grandeur – A delicate yet sophisticated serif that pairs beautifully with modern wedding designs

 Tan Mon Cheri – Soft and whimsical, ideal for a fairytale or garden wedding aesthetic

 Lovelace – A vintage-inspired script font with a graceful, handwritten feel

Whether you’re designing wedding welcome signs, seating charts, or menus, these fonts will bring romance and elegance to your wedding stationery.

As a photographer, some moments leave a lasting imprint on your heart, and this South Indian wedding was one of them. The bride, draped in the finest silk saree with intricate temple jewelry, was the embodiment of grace and beauty—every step she took exuded the timeless elegance of tradition. The groom, on the other hand, was the picture of humility and charm, with a quiet confidence that spoke volumes about his character. Watching them exchange vows amidst the sacred chants and the vibrant hues of a Brahmin wedding was a sight to behold. It wasn't just a union of two souls but a celebration of culture, love, and values that define a perfect South Indian wedding. Capturing these moments felt like freezing a story of devotion and beauty that will be cherished for generations.

REDEFINING RECEPTION LAYOUTS//

Whilst creating an atmosphere of connection at @abbeyfarmweddings with @jacaranda_flowers 

For couples planning a more intimate celebration, this caterpillar style set up is a dream come true! Abbey Farm’s charming rustic beams and cozy space work beautifully with this flowing table arrangement creating a sense of closeness that’s ideal for smaller wedding parties. 

Rather than traditional rows, these interconnecting tables weave through the room, bringing guests together in an elegant, organic way that allows everyone to feel part of the experience. The abundance of candlelight adds warmth and romance, while the delicate florals bring a touch of nature indoors. They are thoughtfully arranged to lead your eye along the captivating snake like flow of the tables. 

The entire space is welcoming, cohesive and effortlessly beautiful. Every guest feels included, every detail feels intentional and every moment becomes unforgettable.

Wedding. Black wedding. Bride to be. Black Bride. Wedding inspo

2025 Brides Listen! These are a few industry secrets that we’d be sharing today.
____
1️⃣YOUR WEDDING WOULD STILL BE SUCCESSFUL  even if it doesn’t go viral on wedding blogs. Going viral is not the test for the best wedding. Did you have fun? That’s all that matters.

2️⃣SOME MONTHS ARE CHEAPER TO GET MARRIED than some others. What’s your wedding month? Drop it in the comments.

3️⃣YOU CAN D-I-Y your way through most things if you cannot afford a Wedding Planner. While wedding Planners are very important, if you’re on a Budget you can do it yourself with the help of friends and family. Or hire an On-The-Day wedding coordinator only. Do you plan to use a wedding planner? Join the conversation in the comments.

4️⃣YOU DO NOT NEED TO SEW/ORDER ALL YOUR CLOTHES! There are more practical and sustainable options like buying preowned outfits and accessories or renting your wedding dress. You can literally rent/hire everything these days.

5️⃣YOU ARE IN CHARGE OF YOUR WEDDING and you decide where to spend heavily on and where to cut costs. Don’t allow anyone gaslight, pressure or push you into doing things you don’t want or spending more than you’ve planned.

6️⃣IT IS POSSIBLE TO DO A SAME DAY EVENT for all aspects of your marriage. That is, Courthouse/Civil, Church, Traditional/Engagement and Reception with the right planning and research.

7️⃣YOU CAN RESELL YOUR USED BRIDAL OUTFITS and recoup some money back. Ending bridal waste is so underrated. The industry is not so concerned about what happens after the wedding but you should! You should be talking to us after your wedding, by the way.
____
So which point is the best kept industry secret? Which one did you find useful. You can drop any more questions you may have in the comments below.
Until next post, do have a lovely evening.

BRIDE GUIDE/Editorial Photography 

In the world of modern weddings, editorial-style photography has emerged as a bold trend, blurring the lines between fashion and fine art. These shoots go beyond capturing moments; they craft visual narratives inspired by timeless aesthetics. One striking example is this shoot by @lens.tales, influenced by the grace of Degas’ ballerinas and the haunting beauty of Tchaikovsky’s Swan Lake.

From layered symbolism to ethereal styling, this editorial draws on intricate storytelling. The towering cake, dramatic shadows, and couture-inspired attire evoke a dreamlike stage where elegance meets fantasy. To achieve such magic, editorial shoots require:
-Impeccable styling: Couture pieces, vintage props, and intentional lighting.
- Visionary direction: A theme rooted in fine art, history, or iconic tales.
- Collaborative artistry: Photographers, designers, and creative directors uniting to create a seamless mood.

Editorial shoots like this one redefine how weddings are remembered, transforming love stories into gallery-worthy masterpieces. Would you dare to dream this bold for your wedding?

A Proud Mum Moment ❤️

Hi everyone,

I’m incredibly proud to introduce one of the key members of Destination Snob , my daughter, Aman. She joined the company nearly two years ago, and today, I couldn’t be prouder of the role she has taken on and the impact she has made.

Aman initially had a completely different path in mind. She earned her degree in Psychology and then went on to complete her Master’s in Forensic Psychology. She always envisioned a 9-5 career… until she saw the world I was part of. Watching me travel, meet incredible people, and create unforgettable weddings around the globe sparked something in her. She decided to step into wedding planning and she hasn’t looked back since.

Today, she’s not just part of the business; she’s a core pillar of it. She’s my right hand, my sounding board, and someone I trust implicitly. The growth of Destination Snob, the seamless execution of our events, and the future of this company wouldn’t be possible without her dedication and passion.

As a mum, there’s no greater feeling than seeing your child recognise the legacy you’ve built and want to be a part of it. Aman has brought fresh ideas, incredible energy, and an unmatched work ethic. And now, with her by my side, I’m more excited than ever for what’s ahead.

So here’s to family, to building something meaningful together, and to the next chapter of Destination Snob hand in hand. ❤️

- Parvy Rakar (@parvyrakar)

Having all of Central Park to ourselves for Sharon & George’s pre-wedding shoot was nothing short of a dream. Sharon looked absolutely breathtaking in this exquisite lehnga by Herpret Couture, perfectly complementing the timeless vibe of New York City.

You’re Truly Missing Out If You’re Not Praying Tahajjud!
I know waking up for Tahajjud isn’t easy, but trust me, it’s worth it. If you haven’t tried it yet, give it a chance. Tahajjud/istighfar is the key to success 

Wake up in the last third of the night, when the world is asleep, and pour your heart out to Allah. Tell Him everything. Make du’a with sincerity, with hope, and with full trust in His wisdom. But here’s an important tip; don’t limit yourself to just one du’a. I repeat ️ don’t limit yourself to just one du’a

Have a list of du’as; things you need in both this life and the Hereafter. This way, as you wait for your biggest du’a to be answered, you’ll start seeing other prayers being granted along the way. This will strengthen your faith, keep you steadfast and give you hope.

Many people give up on making du’a because they focus on one single request, expecting immediate results. And when it doesn’t come as quickly as they hoped, they say, “I’ve prayed and prayed, but Allah hasn’t given it to me,” and they stop asking. But what they don’t realize is that losing hope in Allah is a sin.

When you have a mountain of du’as, you’ll notice the countless ways Allah answers your prayers, some instantly, some over time, and some in ways you never expected. Even if you don’t get the exact thing that initially brought you to your knees, you’ll see His mercy in every other answered prayer.

So don’t give up. Keep making du’a. Keep trusting Allah. Because every du’a is heard, and every sincere call to Him is never wasted. If you find this post useful, pls share so others can benefit. With love @albint_blog 
.

The link is in our bio and story, share your miracles stories to motivate others. Your story might be the reason someone starts praying Tahajjud consistently.

'রাজশাহীর একটা রেস্টুরেন্টে আমাকে প্রথম দেখেছিলো অন্তিক, সেখানে দেখার পর আমাকে ফেসবুকে নক দেয়..! এরপর অনেক কথা দুইজনের ব্যাপারে জানা সবকিছুই হলো ফেসবুকে..!যেই সময়টাই আমার ভালোবাসা বিশ্বাস কোন কিছুর উপর বিশ্বাস ছিলোনা সে সময়ে অন্তিক আসলো জীবনে..! ও থাকতো তখন চুয়েটে আমার জন্য থিসিস এর সময়েও ১৪/১৬ ঘন্টা জার্নি করে রাজশাহী আসতো আবার পরেরদিন চলে যেতো..!
ও আমাকে পাওয়ার জন্যে যা কিছু করা যায় ওর দিক থেকে সব কিছু করেছে..! কখনো বিয়েই করবোনা ভাবা আমাকে ও মানিয়ে ভরসা দিয়ে বিয়ে টা করেছে।
সেই প্রথম দিন থেকে এখন পর্যন্ত এক রকম ভাবে আমার সব ইচ্ছা পূরণ করেছে অন্তিক। এতকিছুর পর ও তো আসলে একটা সুন্দর বউ পেতেই পারে তাই বিয়েটা করে ফেললাম।'
- Behesti Morium

Quando s’immagina un matrimonio da sogno, si pensa a abiti couture, location da favola, allestimenti spettacolari. Eppure, due delle voci di spesa più rilevanti vengono spesso sottovalutate.

AUDIO: è il cuore pulsante di qualsiasi matrimonio. Ogni promessa, ogni discorso, ogni singola nota musicale, devono essere percepiti con assoluta limpidezza, perché la perfezione in questo caso non è un dettaglio!

Questi non sono semplici costi, ma investimenti fondamentali per vivere un’esperienza davvero straordinaria e ricordarla, luminosa e splendida.

How I Create a Traditional Teardrop Bouquet ✨

Watch until the end to see my bride’s inspiration photo and my final design! 

✨This is the only bouquet style I use an oasis holder for, especially since no foliage was used!✨

Here’s how I made it step by step:

1️⃣ Wrap the handle in ribbon first, then cover it with cling film or cellophane to keep it dry.
2️⃣ Place the longest teardrop stems first, I wire these for extra security.
3️⃣ Add larger or softer blooms next, like callas (I wire every calla to prevent mushy stems!).
4️⃣ Fill in the gaps with delicate filler flowers, I used wax flower and gyp for this one.
5️⃣ Check from all angles for gaps, adjust as needed, and voilà!

✨ Inspo vs. Reality: My bride shared a reference photo for inspiration (not my previous work). Every bouquet is unique, and while I match the style and flowers, it’s never an exact replica, especially when it’s another florist’s creation.

What do you think of the final look? Let me know in the comments! ⬇️

2025 Wedding Trends You Need to Know! ✨

Get ready for a year of bold, immersive, and unforgettable wedding experiences! Here’s what’s making waves in 2025:

 Lamps, Lamps, Lamps! Whether it’s elegant table lamps or stunning J-lamps hanging overhead, lighting is setting the mood in a whole new way.

 Guest Immersion Seating – Think circular ceremonies, runway-style aisles, and interactive seating that brings guests closer to the experience.

 Luxury Experience Bars – Espresso martini stations, champagne bars where a ring of a bell gets you a glass, cannoli bars, and even curated bureaus bars for a personalized touch.

 Bold Colors & Statement Decor – Reds, mochas, deep greens—rich, impactful tones are taking center stage for a dramatic, luxe feel.

✨ Draping Beyond the Backdrop – Ceiling draping, full room draping—textiles are transforming spaces for an ultra-romantic ambiance.

 Untraditional Reception Seating – From snake-like table setups to one massive round table for all your guests, seating is becoming part of the experience itself!

2025 is all about creating a wedding that’s not just beautiful—but immersive, unique, and unforgettable. Which trend is your favorite? Let’s chat below! ✨

Bridal Nail Extension Tips Every Bride Must Know! 

Your nails deserve as much attention as your outfit on your big day! Here are essential tips to get that perfect bridal manicure:

1️⃣ Neutral tones are timeless and complement every outfit beautifully.
2️⃣ Medium or short nail length keeps it elegant and practical for all the festivities.
3️⃣ Schedule your nail appointment 2-3 days before your wedding functions to avoid any last-minute hassle.
4️⃣ Choose a nail shape that matches your comfort and enhances your hand’s natural beauty.
5️⃣ Opt for gel nail extensions for a natural and long-lasting finish.

✨ Save this post for your nail prep and share it with brides-to-be! ✨

If you told me 12 years ago that I would enjoy my wedding day without stressing over my blood sugars…

Follow us @diabetesdeann
Follow us @diabetesdeann 

I would have thought you were crazy 

When I was first diagnosed I felt so stuck with my diabetes management. 

I used to be terrified of eating carbs because I was afraid that everytime my sugar went out of range I was going to go blind 

It seemed natural to just stop eating carbs since they impacted my blood sugar the most, but I soon found myself down an obsessive path where food & blood sugars consumed all my thoughts.

I was met with congratulatory pats on the back from my care team because my A1C was great, BUT no one took the time to ask how I was doing mentally or what my relationship with food looked like...

It took me 5 years, 2 degrees, and passing a board exam to truly become an expert in nutrition & diabetes management!

The journey was tough, but I am so grateful to be where I am today. I reflect back on my wedding feeling nothing but pride in how I’ve balanced my diabetes management and LIVING 

And because I want this for you too, I’ve taken everything that I’ve learned to create an extremely high-value, low-cost offer to help you lower your A1C without giving up the foods that you love 

 Eating Essentials 2.0 is here and it’s better than ever!

I’ve merged it with my Eating Out Made Easy course, giving you all the essential information you need for making informed diabetes management decisions for everyday meals and dining out—all in one comprehensive package.

Die schönsten Momente eurer Hochzeit: Die Gratulationen ✨

Die Gratulationen sind für mich einer der emotionalsten und herzlichsten Augenblicke einer Hochzeit. Sie schenken dem Brautpaar die Gelegenheit, die Gäste willkommen zu heißen, Glückwünsche in entspannter Atmosphäre entgegenzunehmen und all die Liebe um sie herum bewusst zu spüren 

In meinem neuen, exklusiven Weddingguide habe ich wertvolle Tipps und Tricks zusammengestellt, um den Hochzeitstag entspannter zu genießen und gleichzeitig wunderschöne Erinnerungen in Form von Fotos zu schaffen. Meine Brautpaare dürfen sich schon bald darüber freuen! 

#hochzeit #hochzeitstag #hochzeitsfotos #hochzeitsfotografie #hochzeitsfotograf #hochzeitsfotografinniederösterreich #carinafritzfotografie #heirateninniederösterreich #trauung #hochzeitsdetails #wedding #weddingphotos #weddingphotography #weddingdetails #weddinginspp #realweddings #realweddingphotos #realweddingdetails

Als Hochzeitsfotografin geht es nicht nur darum schöne Bilder zu machen. Es geht auch darum, echte Emotionen festzuhalten. Während das Brautpaar mitten im Moment lebt, entgehen ihnen oft die kleinen, berührenden Augenblicke ihrer Gäste. Tränen der Rührung, strahlende Lächeln, liebevolle Blicke – all das wird in meinen Bildern für die Ewigkeit eingefangen. So könnt ihr euren großen Tag später noch einmal aus einer ganz neuen Perspektive erleben. 

——

As a wedding photographer, it’s not just about taking beautiful pictures. It’s also about capturing real emotions. While the couple is living in the moment, they often miss the little, touching expressions of their guests—tears of joy, radiant smiles, loving glances. All of these are preserved in my photos for eternity. This way, you can relive your special day from a whole new perspective later on.

PANTONE MOCHA MOUSSE - 2025 COLOUR OF THE YEAR IMAGES// @pantone 

Big shoutout to @darren_cresswell_photography for sending over these stunning images of the Orangery @stubtonhall a couple of weeks ago, love them! 

Mocha mousse is more than a colour, it’s a vibe. It whispers elegance, embraces romance and brings an effortless sophistication your guests will feel the moment they step into the room. 

It creates an inviting, calm ambiance, it’s the perfect mix of cozy and classy. 

When  it comes to styling this look, texture and layering is at the forefront of my mind. Layering textures isn’t just about stacking, it’s about balancing. Think flowing table runners offset by tactile charger plates and shimmering mats, robust velvety blooms paired with delicate silk ribbon and handmade paper, plush napkins against smooth glassware the list goes on and on. 

These thoughtful textures work together to create a look that feels rich, inviting and utterly captivating. Combining different textures creates depth and dimension in your decor and flowers. It’s about creating a feast for the eyes (and the heart) with every detail.

#bacacaption Selain menjemput jodoh dengan cara yang diridhoi oleh Allah, tentu ketika melangsungkan pernikahan harus dengan cara yang diridhoi oleh Allah juga. Banyak di antara kita yang menjemput jodoh sudah sesuai syari'at, tapi ketika melangsungkan acara pernikahan tidak sesuai syari'at. 

Coba bayangkan ketika kamu sudah istiqomah memakai pakaian syar'i, tapi ketika menikah jilbab yang dipakai tidak menutup dada, coba bayangkan ketika kamu sudah komitmen tidak bersentuhan dengan yang bukan mahrom, akhirnya gagal karena muncul rasa tidak enakan ketika salam-salaman, coba bayangkan wajah indah istrimu/suamimu yang seharusnya hanya kamu yang lihat tapi justru jadi konsumsi publik. 

Pernikahan syar'i itu masih sangat tabu, jadi mulai sekarang coba untuk beritahu kepada orang tua kita, konsep menikah sesuai syar'i itu seperti apa. Jika orang tua tidak menyetujui mintalah pertolongan kepada Allah agar meluluhkan hati orang tua kita. 

Mari kita wujudkan pernikahan tanpa musik dan ikhtilat itu ✨

✨ Walimah Syar’i di Rumah dengan Sentuhan Hijau & Gold ✨

Siapa bilang walimah di rumah nggak bisa elegan? Dengan tema hijau & gold, suasana jadi lebih hangat, mewah, tapi tetap syar’i. Tamu tetap nyaman dengan area yang terpisah, dekorasi tetap indah tanpa berlebihan, dan yang terpenting: keberkahan tetap dijaga.

Di Khayr Wedding Syar’i Organizer, kami bantu wujudkan pernikahan impian yang nggak hanya cantik, tapi juga sesuai syariat. Karena pernikahan bukan hanya tentang satu hari, tapi awal perjalanan menuju surga bersama. ✨

Saksi dan Wali dalam Nikah  

Dalam Islam, pernikahan adalah ibadah yang memiliki aturan tersendiri. Salah satu syarat sah nikah adalah adanya wali dan dua saksi yang memenuhi syarat. 

 Urutan Wali Nikah: 
1️⃣ Ayah 
2️⃣ Kakek (ayah dari ayah) 
3️⃣ Saudara laki-laki kandung 
4️⃣ Saudara laki-laki seayah 
5️⃣ Anak dari saudara laki-laki kandung (keponakan) 
6️⃣ Anak dari saudara laki-laki seayah (keponakan) 
7️⃣ Paman (saudara ayah) 
8️⃣ Anak dari paman (sepupu) 

 Syarat Wali dan Saksi: 
✅ Islam 
✅ Baligh (dewasa) 
✅ Berakal 
✅ Merdeka (bukan hamba sahaya) 
✅ Laki-laki 
✅ ‘Adel (bukan orang yang fasik) 

Pastikan wali dan saksi dalam pernikahan memenuhi syarat ini agar akad nikah sah sesuai syariat. ✨ 

 Dengan Nisa’aza, segala persiapan pernikahan syar’i lebih tenang dan terencana. Yuk, konsultasikan kebutuhan pernikahan syar’i Anda bersama kami!

Mengajak anak ke wedding syar’i dapat menjadi momen yang berharga untuk menyisipkan pelajaran agama, antara lain:

1.     
Anak dapat belajar bahwa setiap orang memiliki tanggung jawab menjaga aurat dan berpakaian sesuai syariat, terutama dalam acara besar seperti pernikahan. Contoh dari mempelai dan tamu yang berpakaian syar’i bisa menjadi teladan langsung.

2.    
Jelaskan kepada anak bahwa pernikahan bukan sekadar pesta, tetapi ibadah dan sunnah Rasulullah ﷺ yang membawa pasangan menuju kehidupan yang penuh tanggung jawab, cinta, dan saling melengkapi dalam ketaatan kepada Allah.

3.   
Wedding syar’i biasanya menerapkan pemisahan antara laki-laki dan perempuan. Ini bisa menjadi pelajaran penting tentang adab dalam pergaulan sesuai syariat Islam.

4.    
Anak dapat belajar bahwa mengikuti sunnah Rasulullah ﷺ dalam kehidupan sehari-hari, termasuk dalam pernikahan, mendatangkan keberkahan.

5.   
Anak dapat diajarkan pentingnya mendoakan kebahagiaan dan keberkahan bagi pasangan yang menikah, seperti doa:
“Barakallahu laka wa baraka ‘alaika wa jama’a bainakuma fi khair.”

6.   
Menghadiri acara pernikahan sebagai keluarga juga mengajarkan pentingnya mendukung orang lain dalam kebahagiaan mereka dan menguatkan hubungan kekeluargaan.

We found out from Shann & Jerry that they spend a lot of time together in church and they both loved writing and documenting their feelings and their lives. 

After being part of so many wedding days, we realised how hectic the day can be and couples are rarely able to spend quality time together doing something just for the two of them. So we thought of creating this space for them during their prewedding, where they can truly be with each other and share their vows at a place where they feel most at peace, and at home. 

We imagined it to be beautiful when planning the shoot but watching the moment unfold in person was ten times more beautiful and no words can truly express it. We loved how private it was and how the whole session was an experience as much as it was a photoshoot for them

When Ange (she/her) and Kiki (she/her) began planning their wedding, they envisioned a celebration that was uniquely theirs: a vibrant fusion of their Chinese and Serbian heritages. The highlight of their day? A surprise lion dance that left everyone in awe! ⁠
⁠
Here's a little budget advice/mindset from the newlyweds  ⁠
⁠
 Marry within your means – We started by pulling together various quotes to realistically assess if our wedding dreams matched our budget. We kept a close eye on our finances by routinely updating a dedicated spreadsheet, ensuring no unexpected expenses would surprise us as the big day approached.⁠
⁠
 Spend your pennies purposefully – Over the twelve months of planning, it was tempting to chase after every grand idea that came to mind. However, we consciously decided to reevaluate and redirect our funds towards elements that promised lasting value. We prioritized meaningful, impactful choices that would resonate with us far beyond our wedding day.⁠
⁠
 Invest in your vendors – We believed strongly in investing a significant portion of our budget into our vendors, knowing that their expertise would be crucial. Choosing the right vendors who shared our vision and enthusiasm meant that we could trust them to carry a major part of the wedding day responsibilities, reducing stress and ensuring that our day would be everything we dreamed of.⁠

phew, meet my newest artistic concept and just a little piece of my soul ✨ this location is one of my favorite scenes in the world, set in a UNESCO world heritage site of seemingly never ending rice fields in the middle of Bali. When I was trying to develop a concept for this location, I kept seeing this local farmers hat, worn by the workers to keep the sun off of them in the rice paddies. I could see it in my mind then, a veil, the wind, the infinite reflections. Despite it being in the middle of rainy season, this very morning (there as no backup day, we were shooting rainy or shine) it just happened to give us a life changing sunrise. I still can’t believe it, honestly.  Thank you to the beautiful and kind @vasini_devi for getting up before 3am to model and see this vision through with me

IT’S FINALLY HERE! 

My brand new Wedding Guide is here and I cannot be more excited. This baby is 80+ pages long and absolutely packed with everything I know about planning your wedding day out + the photos that will embody it. 

I go over lighting (indoors and outdoors, natural and artificial). You’ll walk away feeling more in the know of what you can expect from each. Throughout the guide, the wedding day is split into scenes and  for each scene I’ll spill my heart out over all the best advice I’ve gathered through my experience. Instead of sending you a ton of emails (and giving you a yucky amount of screen time), I’ve condensed everything into this PRINTED book for every single one of my wedding couples to have for keeps.

I first created this wedding guide 2 years ago and now that I’ve spent 10 years in the wedding industry - it was time for an update. If you’re curious; you can download a 10 page preview on my website for free. This book will not be sold as it’s completely customized to my style and approach as a photographer, you can consider it a personal lengthy love letter with a step by step on how to plan out your day ensuring you get the dream photos you’ve always been envisioning all while truly ENJOYING every moment of this most special day. 

I’m committed to creating art out of your day, whatever your vision may be. Each day is unique and that’s why I am still (and forever will be) obsessed with wedding pbotography. I’m so here for it. 

I CANNOT WAIT TO CELEBRATE WITH YOU!!

xoxo
Tay

I’m happy to say after more than a decade doing this I’ve served couples from all 50 of the United States of America. From Alaska all the way to Wyoming . It is a joy to get to work with such amazing people and help them create their dream elopement experiences! 

I love chatting with my East coasters about pizza, I love how the Southerners are so polite and call everyone sir & ma’am, I love how the couples from the West coast are so up for adventure and it always makes me happy how the couples from the northern states never worry about our cold weather! 

Here’s a few frames from Marcos & Evelyn’s elopement day. They flew in from Dallas, Texas and they got a gorgeous day on the Causeway Coast. There really isn’t a better place to elope on the planet!

The wedding day is a beautiful tapestry woven from all the little details that come together to create a beautiful picture of love. 

From the intricate lace on the wedding gown to the perfectly placed detail in the centerpieces, each detail brings its own magic to the day.

As the bride prepares for her big day, she carefully selects every detail, each one chosen with the utmost care to express her unique style and personality. The flowers, the centerpieces, the place settings - all selected with love and attention to create the perfect atmosphere of love and celebration.

As the groom awaits his bride, he takes a moment to take in the small details that make the day so special. The way the light pours in through the window, the sound of the music playing softly in the background, and the thoughtfulness of the handwritten card his bride-to-be left for him as a reminder of their love for one another.

Every detail seems to have been placed with the utmost care, right down to the carefully curated menu of the reception dinner. The colors, the textures, and even the scents all work together to create a romantic and relaxed atmosphere.

As the day wears on, the couple can't help but feel overwhelmed by the love that surrounds them. It's the love that's been poured into every detail of their special day that makes it such a memorable and emotional experience for them and their guests. Every detail comes together to create a beautiful picture of their love - and it's something that will stay with them for a lifetime.

As the night draws to a close, the couple takes a last look at every detail of their wedding day. Each detail may seem small on its own, but together they tell the story of their love, their future, and their journey together. It's these little details that make the day so romantic, emotional, and beautiful - a true celebration of love.

Instead of grouping your seating chart by table number, group it by last name (A - Z)

This way, guests don’t need to read through each table to find their name

This is ESPECIALLY important at big weddings!

Träumst du von einer Hochzeit am weißen Sandstrand, in einem romantischen Schloss oder auf einer wilden Klippe mit Blick aufs Meer? Egal, wo du Ja sagst – ich bin für dich da! ❤️

Als Brautstylistin mit fast 20 Jahren Erfahrung reise ich dorthin, wo du mich brauchst. Ob Italien, Spanien, Malediven oder ein kleines verstecktes Paradies – ich sorge dafür, dass du dich wunderschön fühlst, egal, wohin deine Hochzeitsreise geht. ✈️

Sag mir einfach, wo deine Destination Wedding stattfindet, und ich kümmere mich um den Rest. Perfektes Brautstyling – weltweit, stressfrei und mit ganz viel Liebe! ✨

 Schreib mir jederzeit und erzähl mir von deinem Traumort! Ich freu mich riesig darauf, dich an deinem großen Tag zu begleiten. ✨

REDEFINING RECEPTION LAYOUTS//

Whilst creating an atmosphere of connection at @abbeyfarmweddings with @jacaranda_flowers 

For couples planning a more intimate celebration, this caterpillar style set up is a dream come true! Abbey Farm’s charming rustic beams and cozy space work beautifully with this flowing table arrangement creating a sense of closeness that’s ideal for smaller wedding parties. 

Rather than traditional rows, these interconnecting tables weave through the room, bringing guests together in an elegant, organic way that allows everyone to feel part of the experience. The abundance of candlelight adds warmth and romance, while the delicate florals bring a touch of nature indoors. They are thoughtfully arranged to lead your eye along the captivating snake like flow of the tables. 

The entire space is welcoming, cohesive and effortlessly beautiful. Every guest feels included, every detail feels intentional and every moment becomes unforgettable.

FUN FACT: not all gerberas are created equally… 

In my humble florist opinion - I rate the noodle & spider gerbera varieties as the best kinds there are 

For Alissa’s brightly dressed bridesmaids and overall design brief - I couldn’t resist the opportunity to colour coordinate each dress with a perfectly matching en masse noodle gerbera bouquet. It was a VIBE ⚡️
For Ben’s grooms gal - she didn’t miss out on the gerbera party, she had her own unique spider gerbera bouquet 

In comparison to the regular gerbera varieties that everyone recognizes, (and either loves or hates ) - you can’t deny that these bouquets were a perfect fit for Ben & Alissa’s bridal party! 

Also these photos - oh my GOSH I have so many to share of what the amazing @beckrocchiphotography captured from this fun vibrant wedding day! 

Are you a gerbera lover? Let us know in the comments below!

Jess x

저는 성향이 되게 화려하거나 꾸며내는 걸 
잘 못하는 사람이에요.
그냥 자연스러움을 좋아하는 사람이에요.

사진은 개개인의 성향이 강하게 담긴다고 생각해요.
그래서 사진도 항상 자연스럽고 꾸밈없는 두분의 모습을 
담아내려고 노력하고 생각하는 거 같아요

이런 제 사진을 좋아해 주시고 연락 주시는 모든 분들께
항상 감사하다고 말씀드리고 싶네요

매년 좀 더 좋은 사진으로 보답하도록 노력할게요!!!

인스타에 이렇게 소식을 전하는건 처음인것 같아요!
찬란했던 20대 절반을 함께한 저희가 결혼을 하게되었습니다! 시간이 정말 빠르게 지나간다는 걸 실감하게 되네요. 아직도 준비할 것들이 많지만, 하루하루 기쁜 마음으로 다가가고 있습니다. 그래서 이 기쁜소식을 함께 나누고 싶어 글을 쓰게 되었습니다!

제가 자주 연락을 드리지 못했던 분들이나, 소식이 뜸했던 분들께서 혹시나 섭섭해하지 않으실까 걱정돼 이렇게 글을 남깁니다. 언제든 편하게 연락 주신다면 기쁜마음으로 소식 전하겠습니다!

이제 새로운 시작을 앞두고, 그동안 함께 해주신 모든 분들께 진심으로 감사드리며, 앞으로도 계속 좋은 인연으로 함께할 수 있기를 바랍니다

The absolute beauty of the moment

Jasmine and Justin planned their elopement on an incredibly short timeline, but the resulting dockside ceremony last week in New London beside their favorite lobster shack lacked none of the drama, emotion, and weight because of it. We firmly believe that every wedding, no matter how small or seemingly informal, deserves to and should be celebrated and documented. We get just as much out of witnessing weddings with four people and a tiny doggo as we do from 250+ person weddings and we’ll meet you with the exact same enthusiasm and dedication regardless of what your plans end up looking like.

Just two awesome humans, completely themselves, having the best day ever! ❤️ From nonstop laughter to the sweetest little moments, their wedding was all about love, fun, and pure joy. So lucky to have captured it all!

Tuscany is always breathtaking—golden in the summer, misty and romantic in the fall, glowing under any light, in any season. But the true magic? It’s never just about where you are. It’s about who you’re with, the emotions shared, and the love that fills the space. ✨

Capturing Sarah & Stephen’s wedding last September was proof of that. The weather may not have played along, but love doesn’t wait for perfect skies. Their day was filled with warmth, laughter, and the kind of moments that remind me why I do this—because real love stories aren’t about perfection, they’re about feeling everything.

Here’s to celebrating love in all its beautiful, unpredictable forms.

مبدأيا القلعة فيها ٤ أماكن متاحين لكتب الكتاب زي ما متوضحين ف الفيديو بأسعارهم و الاسعار في الفيديو شاملة جولف كار توصل الناس من الباب لحد مكان الevent + تصوير ساعة في مواعيد العمل الرسمية

* تأمين شرطة السياحة لا يسترد و بيتم دفع تأمين تاني ٢٥٪ ده بيسترد تاني بعد الايفينت

* بالنسبة لأول مكان مسجد سليمان باشا متاح حجزه من إدارة العلاقات الثقافية في العباسية و بيتحجز لمدة ساعتين فقط و ممنوع فيه أي اغاني خالص

* تاني مكان و أشهرهم هو ساحة مسجد محمد علي بيتحجز من شركة كنوز موجودين ف القلعة كل يوم ماعدا الجمعة من الساعة ١٠ ل ٤ و المكان بيتحجز لمدة ٣ ساعات و مسموح ب soft music بس و البوفيه fingerfood

* تالت و رابع مكان (دار الضرب و بير يوسف) برضو الحجز بيكون من شركة كنوز ف القلعة و مسموح بأغاني (مش مهرجانات و مش شعبي) و البوفيه fingerfood او setmenu او openbuffet 

و آخر حاجة عشان الناس دايما بتسأل مفروض تحجز قبلها بقد إيه فأنصحكوا تحجزوا مجرد ما تحددوا الشهر حتي لو فاضل مدة كبيرة تقدروا تحجزوا عادي عشان تضمنوا تواريخ فاضية مناسبة

✨BIG NEWS + 2023 BOOKING UPDATE✨

We are so excited to share BIG news with you! After many months of back and forth, research, and a whole lot of dreaming, we made the leap to invest in a laser cutter. If you aren’t familiar with the world of custom signage - this means that all of our work is about to get a little bit more ✨e x t r a✨ and we are so excited to share them with you!

Here’s some of the changes we’ll be making:

• Our mirror rental inventory is here to stay - always! However, all acrylic and wood signage will be getting a sweet upgraded look that we cannot wait to share 

• You’ll be able to see sneak peeks of our new products and offerings over the next few weeks as we begin to create for some beautiful weddings this month!

• In the meantime, we are not accepting new events for 2023 until the end of August/early September (exact date TBD). Any inquiries placed in the meantime will be replied to when we reopen for bookings. If you’ve already inquired, you got in right in time!

• This does mean we will need to increase our pricing to reflect the increased cost of materials and service provided, but all couples who have already booked are locked into their current pricing and services unless they would like to upgrade to our new style. 

We are so beyond excited to start this next chapter of creating for you guys! We couldn’t have made this step without the support of all of you. So truly, thank you 

If you have any questions, drop them below or send an email to emily@somethingborrowedeventdecor.com

Colorful or neutral—what’s your Mehndi tablescape style? 

Tablescapes are an extension of the event’s focal point (usually the stage!) and help create a cohesive vibe. The key? Knowing how to pull the right colors and layer them thoughtfully.

For Mehndis, you can either pull colors from the stage for the linens or opt for a neutral base and add pops of color with accents like napkins.

✨  Swipe for a walkthrough of examples from our designs!

What do you prefer—colorful or neutral? Let us know in the comments!

Regardless, the trick is layering and balance. Every detail, from linens to napkins, matters!

Custom napkins with ✨ embroidered, and satin bows with guest name embroidered in metallic gold ✨

 This is just the truth...

If you want to book luxury weddings you have to *show* luxury. It’s as simple as that. 

But how do you get your foot in the door? I know it’s so hard when you start, I’ve been there too! I built my portfolio slowly over many years and now exclusively book beautiful weddings. 

 Firstly, you can attend portfolio building workshops! You really are spoilt for choice now - make sure the mood board, models and venue are exactly what you need and invest in yourself.

‍♀️ Put on your own styled shoots - this requires a lot more of your time and financial investment usually but always worth it. Focus on luxury details, the table scape matters - don’t compromise on it!
 Align yourself & your brand with luxury experiences. Have you ever watched my stories over at @poppycarterportraits? You’ll notice I always post when I’m at soho house, drinking champagne or visiting the Ritz in Paris. This isn’t to show off - it’s to align myself with my ideal client. My life looks like that maybe 5% of the time but on social media it’s part of my brand identity.
 Put simply, you cannot sell what you do not show. 
.

Some tips for a more eco-friendly wedding 

1. If you’re having an international wedding like me, consider off setting the flights for your guests who are flying over. You can pay to 'offset' or make up for the emissions that their flights produce by planting a certain amount of trees. Some airlines now offers the options as well when booking your flight. The app that I recommend for this is called @withaerial 

2. For wedding invitations, consider going digital. Much better for the planet and it will saves your ass during a pandemic; in case you have to postpone your wedding a couple of times like us  Plus I mean seriously, who keeps paper invitations these days? I loved the design of our digital invitations, our guest were impressed! I recommend @greenvelope 

3. For menu and name tags; use plantable seed paper. Your guests can plant them later in their garden and eventually see beautiful flowers growing out of it!

4. For your bridesmaids dresses; I recommend renting or buying second hand if you can.
Renting: @hirestreetuk (best bridesmaids options) @byrotationofficial 
Buying second hand: @depop @vinted @bridalreloved @bride2bride.co.uk @recycle.my.wedding 

5. Opt for a vegetarian or vegan menu only. Food will be as delicious I promise. “Oxford university study concluded that eating vegan can reduce your carbon footprint by 73%” - online research 

6. Promote local & in season produces. Try to use local and fresh ingredients, that are in seasons for your food menu. Why buy seasonal Ingredients? It helps to stimulate the economy, you avoid creating pollution by having your products shipped from another country and your food is a lot fresher, tastier and more nutritious. Same goes for your flowers - seasonal flowers for the win!

Don’t forget that these are just suggestions, it’s impossible to have a perfect eco-friendly wedding, all you can do is try your best to not make it less wasteful and try to avoid being part of the problem. 

Any more tips please share below!

DON'T BE FOOLED... 

How many times have you seen other cake makers or wedding suppliers say something like this in the last week: 

"Back on admin today, I have had so many enquiries over Christmas," 

Or 

"Can't believe how many new enquiries I have had over the Christmas break" 

And you checked your inbox to pure tumbleweed and crickets and wonder what it is you are doing wrong. 

Don't worry. The majority are likely exactly the same. 

We say these sorts of things for a few reasons, to generate urgency and make clients think "oh no I best book quick", to self present and make it look good for the business, or just out of habit and common phrase. 

Don't get me wrong. There will be some that do get enquiries over Christmas, in the wedding industry maybe your venues, but for the majority, clients are unlikely sending enquiries over Christmas, they are getting 5 glasses deep in mulled wine and camenbert, hiding in the bathroom from annoying family members and children and sleeping off a hangover. January you will likely see more. 

 Any Christmas engagements will NOT be contacting cake makers when they don't even have a date or a venue, so DO NOT WORRY. 

When you see people post things like this, take it with a pinch of salt, it doesn't mean you are doing something wrong... 

Anyway, I have to get on with the piles of admin and enquiries from the Christmas break.. SPEAK SOON

ATTENTION ALL WEDDING PROS:

Does your website make it obvious that you are inclusive, affirming, and celebrate the LGBTQ+ community?

It might seem obvious to you, but that’s not the case for the many LGBTQ+ couples who often have to “dig” in order to find the right vendors and venues for their engagements, weddings, elopements, etc.

For many of these couples, meeting with a vendor they’re unsure will respect their identities and celebrate their love can be extremely anxiety-inducing.

Here is a tip that will help couples clear up any doubts they may have and prevent you from contributing to their anxiety:

➡️ Add that you are LGBTQ+ inclusive on your website. ⬅️

Making this as clear as possible on your website will not only make LGBTQ+ couples and marriers feel excited about reaching out to you, they will feel more comfortable as well.

Try it out and let us know what you think in the comments.

To learn more about how you can authentically serve the LGBTQ+ community, enroll in our LGBTQ+ Inclusive Certification Course by heading to the link in our bio!

I can’t wait to marry you  
In weniger als 3 Monaten werden wir einfach offiziell Mann & Frau sein. Bei den ganzen Foto Shootings, wo wir unsere Rollen gespielt haben sind bereits so wunderschöne Fotos & Videos entstanden. Ich kann mir glaub gar nicht vorstellen wie viel mir die Aufnahmen unseres besonderen Tages & den ECHTEN Emotionen bedeuten werden  Auch wenn man es kaum sagen darf, haben wir aktuell einfach noch nicht fix jemanden, der unser Civil Wedding Concept am 9. September begleiten wird  Ich bin ja immer Team “trust the universe” & alles kommt wie es kommen soll  Also lets see was sich in unserer Hochzeits-Planungs Bubble noch alles ergibt  PS: We Are Young dumb and broke and can barely afford anything

✨GEWINNSPIEL✨ - BEENDET -

Die kuscheligste Zeit des Jahre ist da und damit neigt sich 2023 auch schon dem Ende zu. Ich durfte dieses Jahr wieder ganz viele tolle Menschen kennenlernen, wiedersehen und ganz wundervolle Momente festhalten. Das alles würde garnicht gehen ohne euch und ich bin euch unheimlich dankbar dafür, dass mein zweites Jahr in der Selbstständigkeit SO schön war! 
Daher möchte ich euch gerne etwas zurückgeben und verlose hiermit einmal mein Shootingpaket „A BIT MORE“ inkl. 30 bearbeiteten Fotos (bis zu 4 Personen)! Egal ob mit eurem Herzmenschen, eurem kleinen Wunder oder nur für euch alleine. 

Das Gewinnspiel läuft bis zum 31.12.2023.

Was ihr dafür tun müsst:
- folgt mir auf Instagram
- verlinkt jemanden, der sich auch über das Shooting freuen würde
- speichert den Beitrag
- für die doppelte Gewinnchance: teilt den Beitrag in eurer Story (verlinkt mich aber, sonst kann ich die Story nicht sehen ☺️)

Ich drücke euch die Daumen! ✨

Dss Shooting findet in München/Umgebung oder Lichtenfels/Umkreis statt. Mit der Teilnahme erklärt ihr euch mit Veröffentlichung der Bilder einverstanden.

Das Gewinnspiel steht in keinem Zusammenhang mit Instagram. Der/die Gewinner*in wird nach Auslosung per DM benachrichtigt. Deine Daten werden nur für dieses Gewinnspiel verwendet. Eine Barauszahlung und der Rechtsweg sind ausgeschlossen.

Blumen spielen eine zentrale Rolle bei Hochzeiten und tragen maßgeblich zur Atmosphäre und zum Gesamteindruck des großen Tages bei. Sie sind nicht nur ein schöner visueller Akzent, sondern symbolisieren auch Liebe, Freude und neues Leben. Hier sind einige wichtige Aspekte zu Blumenarrangements und Brautsträußen, die eure Hochzeit unvergesslich machen können.

1. Brautsträuße: Der Brautstrauß ist eines der bedeutendsten Blumenarrangements der Hochzeit. Er sollte nicht nur die Persönlichkeit der Braut widerspiegeln, sondern auch harmonisch zum Hochzeitskleid und zum Gesamtkonzept der Feier passen. Beliebte Blumen für Brautsträuße sind Rosen, Pfingstrosen, Lilien und Orchideen. Die Wahl der Farben kann von zarten Pastelltönen bis hin zu kräftigen, lebhaften Farben reichen, je nach Stil und Thema der Hochzeit. Ein trendiger Ansatz ist es, den Brautstrauß mit persönlichen Elementen zu versehen, wie zum Beispiel einem Familienerbstück oder einem kleinen Anhänger mit einer besonderen Botschaft.

2. Blumen für den Bräutigam und die Trauzeugen: Auch der Bräutigam und die Trauzeugen sollten nicht vergessen werden. Ein passendes Boutonnière, das aus einer kleinen Blume oder einem grünen Akzent besteht, ergänzt das Outfit des Bräutigams und harmoniert mit dem Brautstrauß.

Egal, für welche Blumenarrangements und Brautsträuße ihr euch entscheidet, wichtig ist, dass sie eure Persönlichkeit und den Stil eurer Hochzeit widerspiegeln. Blumen sind nicht nur Dekoration, sie erzählen eine Geschichte und schaffen Erinnerungen, die ein Leben lang halten.
